<font size =+2><B>Pittsburgh Opera: </B></font size> <BR>
Celebrating its 57th season, Pittsburgh Opera has been under the general direction of Tito Capobianco since 1983. In 1987, Benedum Center became the permanent home for the Pittsburgh Opera and the Pittsburgh Opera Orchestra was formed. Pittsburgh Opera prides itself on casting international artists and international debut artists. Opera Camerata, the performing arm of the Pittsburgh Opera center at Duquesne (young artist program), encourages future stars while offering opera performances in the tristate communities.<BR>Pittsburgh Opera<BR>711 Penn Avenue, 8th Floor<BR>Pittsburgh, Pa. 15222-3407<BR>tel. (412) 281-0912; fax (412) 281-4324<BR>Vincent A. Sarni, Co-Chairman<BR>Thomas H. O'Brien, Co-Chairman<BR>Ritchie Scaife, President<BR>Oct. 7-15, 1995<BR>Verdi's Aida<BR>Nov. 4-12, 1995<BR>Strauss' Der Rosenkavalier<BR>March 9-17, 1996<BR>Mozart's Cosi fan tutte<BR>April 13-21, 1996<BR>Mascagni's Cavalleria Rusticana<BR>Leoncavallo's Pagliacci
