<font size =+2><B>Pittsburgh Public Theater: </B></font size> <BR>
Pittsburgh Public Theater strives to produce professional theater of the highest quality in order to challenge, stimulate and entertain a diverse audience in a six-play season from October through July. The Public is also committed to reaching nontraditional audiences and young   people through outreach and education programs.<BR>Pittsburgh Public Theater<BR>Allegheny Square<BR>Pittsburgh, Pa. 15212<BR>tel. (412) 323-8200; fax (412) 323-8550<BR>Stephen Klein, Managing Director<BR>Edward Gilbert, Artistic Director<BR>Founded 1974<BR>Oct. 12  Nov. 19, 1995<BR>Amazing Grace<BR>Nov. 22  Dec. 31, 1995<BR>The Complete History of America and<BR>The Bible: The Complete Works of God
