<font size =+2><B>Pittsburgh Symphony Orchestra: </B></font size> <BR>
The Pittsburgh Symphony is celebrating its 100th anniversary during the 1995-96 season. <P> The Pittsburgh Symphony Society strives to attain the highest standards of artistic achievement. It wants to reach and make available to all segments of the community live symphonic music in order to provide artistic entertainment and educational opportunities. The Symphony wants to present the finest in classical symphonic music programming with an appropriate blend of contemporary works by the finest contemporary composers. It also wants to sustain and improve the fiscal strength of the Society to meet its goals and to maintain fiscal integrity. <P> The Symphony annually presents 24 weeks of classical subscription concerts, seven four-concert sets of Pops concerts, special holiday concerts, Fiddlesticks family concert series, plus a series of educational concerts. The Symphony provides free-admission concerts in the parks plus a series of Community Outreach Concerts throughout southwestern Pennsylvania. <BR>Pittsburgh Symphony Orchestra<BR>600 Penn Avenue<BR>Pittsburgh, Pa. 15222<BR>tel. (412) 392-4800;	  fax (412) 392-4909<BR>Lorin Maazel, Music Director<BR>Richard P. Simmons, Chairman<BR>Founded 1896<BR>Pittsburgh Symphony Orchestra <BR>Sept. 15-17, 1995<BR>Beethoven<BR>Lorin Maazel, conductor<BR>April 18-21, 1996<BR>Andres Cardenes, violin<BR>Hilary Hahn, violin<BR>Sept. 21-23, 1995<BR>Strauss, Hindemith and Chopin<BR>Leslie B. Dunner, conductor<BR>Horacio Gutierrez, piano<BR>Oct. 6-8, 1995<BR>Wagner's Tristan und Isolde, Act III<BR>Lorin Maazel, conductor<BR>Oct. 12-15, 1995<BR>Gould, Mercadante, Maazel and Bartok<BR>Lorin Maazel, conductor<BR>James Galway, flute<BR>Oct. 19-21, 1995<BR>Sibelius, Mendelssohn and Strauss<BR>Lorin Maazel, conductor<BR>Yo-Yo Ma, cello<BR>Nov. 9-12, 1995<BR>Berlioz's Harold in Italy and Ravel's Daphnis et Chloe<BR>Charles Dutoit, conductor<BR>Randolph Kelly, viola<BR>Mendelssohn Choir of Pittsburgh<BR>Nov. 17-19, 1995<BR>Creston, Ibert and Strauss<BR>Marek Janowski, conductor<BR>Nov. 24-26, 1995<BR>Haydn, Paganini and Stravinsky<BR>Sian Edwards, conductor<BR>Ingolf Turban, violin<BR>Nov. 30  Dec. 3, 1995<BR>Schubert, Grieg and Dvorak<BR>Heinz Wallberg, conductor<BR>Hae-Jung Kim, piano<BR>Dec. 8-10, 1995<BR>Copland, St.-Saens, Ben-Shabetai and Debussy<BR>Kirk Muspratt, conductor<BR>Elmar Oliveira, violin<BR>Dec. 14-16, 1995<BR>Bach Christmas Oratorio<BR>Robert Page, conductor<BR>Mendelssohn Choir of Pittsburgh<BR>Jan. 5-7, 1996<BR>Mozart<BR>Pinchas Zukerman, conductor and violinist<BR>Jan. 19-21, 1996<BR>Ravel, Vaughan Williams and Shostakovich<BR>Andre Previn, conductor<BR>Cynthia Koledo DeAlmeida, oboe<BR>Jan. 25-27, 1996<BR>Haydn, Beethoven, Copland and Previn<BR>Andre Previn, conductor<BR>Ignat Solzhenitsyn, piano<BR>Feb. 29  March 3, 1996<BR>Schubert, Beethoven and Mendelssohn<BR>Lorin Maazel, conductor<BR>Murray Perahia, piano<BR>March 15-17, 1996<BR>Borodin, Khachaturian and Shostakovich<BR>Kirk Muspratt, conductor<BR>James Ehnes, violin<BR>March 21-23, 1996<BR>Mozart and Bruckner<BR>Christoph Eschenbach, conductor and pianist<BR>March 29-31, 1996<BR>Handel, Schurmann and Berlioz<BR>Ulf Schirmer, conductor<BR>April 12-14, 1996<BR>Read, St.-Saens, Stock and Scriabin<BR>Lorin Maazel, conductor<BR>Awadagin Pratt, piano<BR>April 18-21, 1996<BR>Menotti, Beethoven and J. Strauss<BR>Lorin Maazel, conductor<BR>Emanuel Ax, piano<BR>April 26-28, 1996<BR>Britten, Picker, Puccini and Verdi<BR>Lorin Maazel, conductor<BR>Barbara Hendricks, soprano<BR>Carol Wincenc, flute<BR>May 2-4, 1996<BR>Maazel, Ravel and Hindemith<BR>Lorin Maazel, conductor<BR>Mstislav Rostropovich, cello<BR>May 9-12, 1996<BR>Brahms<BR>Lorin Maazel, conductor<BR>Yefim Bronfman, piano<BR>May 17-19, 1996<BR>Mahler's Symphony No. 2 Resurrection<BR>Lorin Maazel, conductor<BR>Sharon Sweet, soprano<BR>Markella Hatziano, mezzo-soprano<BR>Mendelssohn Choir of Pittsburgh<BR>Pittsburgh Symphony Pops Series<BR>Sept. 28  Oct. 1, 1995<BR>Passionate Music from Stage and Screen ... <BR>Marilyn Horne, mezzo-soprano<BR>John Tesh, piano<BR>Marvin Hamlisch, conductor<BR>Nov. 2-5, 1995<BR>The Manhattan Rhythm Kings<BR>Kirk Muspratt, conductor<BR>Dec. 17-23, 1995<BR>A Wonderful World of Christmas<BR>Arthur Post, conductor<BR><BR><BR>Jan. 11-14, 1996<BR>Catch Tomorrow's Stars Today ...<BR>Marvin Hamlisch, conductor<BR>March 7-10, 1996<BR>John Williams<BR>May 30-June 2, 1996<BR>Bobby McFerrin<BR>June 27-30, 1996<BR>Celebrate a Prom Night from Yesteryear ...<BR>The Platters<BR>Marvin Hamlisch, conductor<P>Information for the  Performing Arts Guide was compiled by Susan Steranchak.	
