<TITLE>To The Point: </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<a href="http://www.pittsburgh.net/cgi-bin/imagemap/ERBanner">
<IMG BORDER=0 ALIGN=bottom SRC="../pictures/Departments.TP.gif" ISMAP></a>
<p>
<hr>
"The company recent-ly was the successful bidder to provide coverage, effective [this month], for a large manufacturer in its West Virginia and Ohio locations. Utilizing this anchor tenant as a base, along with our resources from our Pittsburgh hub, we anticipate a successful expansion into these two states."<br>
- <b>Philip Hertik</b>, president and CEO, Coventry Corp. (parent of HealthAmerica Pittsburgh)<p>

<hr>"High technology represents a very large segment of the advertising world. It is very important for those involved in media planning activities for these products and services to speak in a unified voice. ITMAC provides that voice."<br>
- <b>Michael F. Walsh</b>, senior vice president and director of finance and operations for Ketchum Advertising Pittsburgh and new chairman of the Information Technology Media Advisory Council trade organization<p>
<hr>
"Firms that are floundering about, mixing and matching managerial ingre-dients with little rhyme or reason except that, The other guys do it, and they're doing OK,' may not survive."<br>
- <b>Charles C. Snow</b>, Ph.D. and management researcher, Penn State University<p>
<hr>
"Over 25 million Americans - 80% of them women - are affected by osteoporosis which results in bone loss and weakening of the bones."<br>
- <b>Dr. Francis X. Solano Jr</b>., medical director of the Osteoporosis Prevention & Treatment Center at Magee-Womens Hospital<p>
