<font size =+2><B>About the Rankings</B></font size> 
The 1995 Pennsylvania 100 represents the largest non-financial public companies in the commonwealth, ranked by 1994 revenues. There are some other criteria, too: The company must be headquartered in Pennsylvania, and it must be actively traded on the New York Stock Exchange, the American Stock Exchange, the NASDAQ National Market System or over the counter.
The earnings figures are "as reported," which includes all extraordinary charges and income. All figures for 1993 have been adjusted.
This year, the Pennsylvania 100 was compiled by John Frankola, Al Madison and Steven Baumgarten of Parker/Hunter Inc., Pittsburgh.
