<TITLE> To The Point</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<a href="http://www.pittsburgh.net/cgi-bin/imagemap/ERBanner">
<IMG BORDER=0 ALIGN=bottom SRC="../pictures/Departments.TP.gif" ISMAP></a>
<p>
<HR>
"Poverty takes a toll on education. This region must come together to address poverty's dev-astating impact."<B>-- Felicia Lynch, president, Allegheny Policy Council</B>
<HR> 
"In many ways, it is as unanswerable as the old chicken-and-egg question -- which comes first, more natural gas vehicles or more refueling stations? You won't see more refueling stations until there are more vehicles, but the opposite is true too. You won't see more people driving NGVs [natural gas vehicles] until they know there are places where they can fill their tanks."<B>-- Kenneth T. Cuccinelli, vice president of marketing and technology, CNG</B>
<HR>
"One of the biggest mistakes I've seen people make is to try to save money by hiring an independent housekeeper. Besides setting yourself up for an IRS audit, you risk damage to your most important investment -- your home. If there's a theft, you have no effective recourse. And should the worker get injured on the job, your homeowner's insurance probably won't cover it."<B>-- Harry Edgar, owner of The Maids</B>
<HR>
"A typical audit will question specific in-come or expense items and ask for documen-tation only on those amounts. But the super audit will question every single line of your tax return. You'll have to provide documentation on every item."<B>-- Emanuel V. DiNatale, CPA, Alpern, Rosenthal & Co., on the IRS' new taxpayer compliance measurement program</B>
<HR>
"Over the next few years, a lot of [companies] will be claiming to have re-engineered. In reality, most will be using it as a description for just shuffling the chairs. Or worse, using it as a camouflage for downsizing."<B>-- Tony Bucci, president and CEO, MARC Advertising</B>
<HR>
"Our audience is drawn from four states, and this tremendous increase in sales is testament to the growing popularity of ballet as an art form the entire family can enjoy."<B>-- Steven Libman, managing director, Pittsburgh Ballet Theatre on the annual Nutcracker performance</B>
