<p>
<HR>
"In the year since Act 44 went into effect, we have seen an average decrease in workers' compensation insurance premiums of 4.66%, and many premium rates have dropped by 6[%] to 10%."<BR>
<B>Robert S. Barnett, secretary, Pennsylvania Labor and Industry</B>
<HR>
<P>
"In the end, the Clinton effort to reform healthcare died because no one wanted to pay for it."<BR>
<B>Dr. Bruce L. Wilder, private practice physician and associate editor of the Allegheny County Medical Society's Bulletin</B>
<HR>
"It's time for productivity, not pay raises."<BR>
<B>Gov. Robert P. Casey (who leaves office this month), 
	on vetoing pay raises for state lawmakers</B>

<HR>
"Despite our recent operational successes, a growing concern is a recent sharp upturn in steel imports - much of it subsidized and dumped in the U.S. market. Steel sheet imports in July rose to nearly 24% of domestic consumption, compared with about 18% in the first half of 1994."<BR>
<B>Charles A. Corry, chairman, USX Corp.</B>
<HR>
"For years, entrepreneur-ship programs have in-volved business start-ups. But of the companies that overcome initial problems successfully, only a small proportion sustain their initial success and go on to become continuously growing businesses."<BR>
<B>Lawrence T. McGeehan, president, Ben Franklin 
	Technology Center of Western Pennsylvania</B>
<HR>
"Hiring people with disabilities is good business. Studies and experience show that people with disabilities rank extremely high on the job in productivity and attendance."<BR>
<B>Denise M. Brownlee, deputy secretary for 
	administration, Pennsylvania Labor and Industry</B>
<HR>
"The formation of a number of smaller community banks will provide us with a more customer responsive, competitive organization and will make our already successful banking franchise even better."<BR>
<B>-	Leonard M. Carroll, president and chief operating 
	officer, Integra Financial Corp., on the restructuring of 
	the organization to seven to nine community banks in 
	western Pennsylvania under single state chartered 
	Integra Bank</B>
