<HTML>
  <!--Written by Rob Herbert-->
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 235</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 235</H1>
      <P>March 1996</P>
    </CENTER>
    <HR>
     <IMG BORDER=2 ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="cover.jpg" ALT="[Magazine Cover]">
    <DL>
      <DT><IMG SRC="../bullet.gif" HSPACE=5><A HREF="comment.htm">Commentary</A>
          <DD><B>Canary Dwarves:</B> Is John Major's stance on Northern Ireland all it's cracked up to be?
          <DD><B>Plus &ccedil;a Change:</B> How should Liberal Democrats react to &quot;New&quot; Labour?
      <DT><IMG SRC="../bullet.gif" HSPACE=5><A HREF="rb.htm">Radical Bulletin</A>
      <DT><IMG SRC="../bullet.gif" HSPACE=5><A HREF="reviews.htm">Reviews</A>
      <DT><IMG SRC="../bullet.gif" HSPACE=5><A HREF="1.htm">The Back-Door Death Penalty</A>
        <DD>Lord Russell explains that Liberals should cherish the Welfare State, because if the State demands peoples' allegiance, it has a duty to keep them alive.
        <DT><I>Cover: S. G. Rayment</I>
    </DL>
