  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 235 Radical Bulletin</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG WIDTH=100% SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 235</H1>
      <BR CLEAR=ALL><HR>
      <H1><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="../rb.gif">Radical Bulletin</H1>
    </CENTER>

    <H2><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="../rb2.gif">On The Doorstep</H2>
    <P>Kennington is a south London suburb which compensates for its general insalubrity by its proximity to Westminster. It is thus the London hang-out of Paddy Ashdown and of many other luminaries of politics.</P>
    <P>Three very prominent Liberal Democrats were making their way through the neighbourhood one recent night when they were obliged to halt abruptly to make way for a rather upmarket car, which had just moved off nearby, and swished imperiously past. In it they recognised Labour leader Tony Blair. As they rounded the next corner, hard by Ashdown Towers, who should they see but Ashdown himself, standing on his doorstep with the appearance of one who has just seen off a guest. They speculated that Blair had been invited in for a birthday drink (which they had not).</P>
    <HR>
    <H2><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="../rb2.gif">Turning Thurnham</H2>
    <P>As of early March former Tory MP Peter Thurnham is sitting as an Independent and not as a Liberal Democrat. And the local party in Westmoreland and Lonsdale has made it clear that it would not be prepared to evict its current PPC to make way for Thurnham to be a Liberal Democrat candidate there, a course of action redolent of Westminster hothouse plotting.</P>
    <P>That is how it should be. Although Thurnham probably falls into a broad swathe of people who are not too bad as Tories go, there is nothing to suggest that he has changed his mind and become a Liberal Democrat. Indeed, he has not claimed to have done so.</P>
    <P>The main reason given for his grievance with the Tories was his failure to make the Westmoreland short-list, rather than fundamental issues of principle, as appeared to be the case with Emma Nicholson.</P>
    <P>There were talks with the Liberal Democrats, and senior party figures seem to have played a key role in Thurnham's final decision to leave the Tories.</P>
    <P>But 'Independent Conservative' seems a wholly accurate description of Thurnham. The Liberal Democrats cannot credibly start offering a home to every Tory miffed about missing out on a seat selection.</P>
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border2.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <A HREF="http://www.liberator.org.uk/cgi-bin/imagemap/imagemaps/buttons.map"><IMG SRC="../buttons.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#BUTTONS" ISMAP></A>
