  <!--Written by Rob Herbert-->
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 233 Reviews</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 233 Reviews</H1>
      <BR CLEAR=ALL><HR>
      <H2>The Flood System</H2>
      <H3>by Geoff Tansey  & Tony Worsley.<BR>Earthscan 1995 15.95</H3>
    </CENTER>
    <P>Money may make the world go around, but it is food (and water) that keeps us alive.  Of course, as agriculture has become increasingly commercialised, the two things have become inseparably mixed.  But "The Food System" goes way beyond being just another expose of the ain't-it'awful world of agribusiness and how huge companies make fortunes out of our need to eat, while screwing the Third World in the process.</P>
    <P>In fact, Tansey and Worsley have produced a kind of mini-encyclopedia on anything and everything to do with the food system, even though the sections are not set out alphabetically.  There are lively chapters on major themes, amply supplemented with little boxes on separate items, pie-charts, tables of often esoteric but utterly riveting information, including what ancient peoples included in their diets.</P>
    <P>Far from being academic in style (despite its serious intention), the book fizzes and entertains like a really well-written Focus leaflet, showing just how good a product one can produce with wit and imagination, hard facts and a good computer.</P>
    <P ALIGN=RIGHT><B>Jonathan Fryer</B></P>
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border2.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <A HREF="http://www.liberator.org.uk/cgi-bin/imagemap/imagemaps/buttons.map"><IMG SRC="../buttons.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#BUTTONS" ISMAP></A>
