<HTML>
  <!--Written by Rob Herbert-->
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 233 Reviews</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 233 Reviews</H1>
      <BR CLEAR=ALL><HR>
      <H2>The Electoral System in Britain</H2>
      <H3>by Robert Blackburn<BR>MacMillan 1995</H3>
    </CENTER>
    <P>Blackburn opens by reminding us that "Few subjects in politics are as important as the way in which the people of a country choose those who will govern them". Most commentators from Herodotus onwards concur with this.</P>
    <P>At its most simple level Blackburn presents us with a comprehensive, factual and in the main, accurate textbook. His subject is brought as close to the present as the constraints of publishing allow. Thus at one point he cites Sanders and another vs. Chichester and another (11.11.1994) - of Literal Democrat notoriety, whereas on the subject of corrupt and illegal practices in elections he closes on Regina vs. Rowe, ex-parte Mainwaring and another (21.1.1991) which decision was overturned on appeal (and I believe has had one further citation in the development of caselaw on such matters since). Keep those donations coming in... Tower Hamlets Liberal Democrats Action Trust , 8 Chisenhale Road, London E3 5QZ.</P>
    <P>Ignore the dryness of this review, we are not dealing with a legalistic text here and the cases mentioned above only serve to underline the currency of the book. A fair body of the work is essentially received information, but this is spiced with a wealth of anecdote making it to my confessed surprise, readable. I will however confess that my lifelong indifference was maintained to the 67 pages on electoral reform and proportional representation.</P>
    <P>As an agent I find this book useful, as a politician to not be able to dip into it and be hooked is to have missed something. Students - essential. The index is weak, but the subject organisation of the work should overcome this.</P>
    <P ALIGN=RIGHT><B>S G Rayment</B></P>
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border2.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <A HREF="http://www.liberator.org.uk/cgi-bin/imagemap/imagemaps/buttons.map"><IMG SRC="../buttons.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#BUTTONS" ISMAP></A>
