<HTML>
  <!--Written by Rob Herbert-->
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 233 Reviews</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 233 Reviews</H1>
      <BR CLEAR=ALL><HR>
      <H2>Interesting Times</H2>
      <H3>by Terry Pratchett<BR>Corgi 1995 4.99</H3>
    </CENTER>
    <P>Not exactly, I regret... see my last review of the Pratchett oeuvre (<IMG SRC="../name.gif" ALT="Liberator"> 230). Yet is this unfair, here we have the academia of the Unseen University, Rincewind, Cohen the Barbarian; Twoflower makes a return, but the development of these characters lacks something I feel.</P>
    <P>Let us call the Agatean Empire (of the Counterweight Continent) China, then the main thread of the story is what is commonly known about Chinese history. The juxtaposition of "Red Army" with terra-cotta soldiers is brilliant, and around it fragments of Pratchett's political philosophy fall into place. Basically scepticism of those who would seek to speak for "the people" (who invariably didn't request such generosity). Rincewind waxes lyrically on the subject...</P>
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
      <P>'All those people out in the fields...if you have a revolution it'll be better for them....?' 'Of course', said Butterfly, 'They will no longer be subject to the cruel whims of the Forbidden City.'</P>
      <P>'Oh that's good', said Rincewind. 'So they'll sort of be in charge of themselves, will they?'</P>
      <P>'Indeed' said Lotus Blossom.</P>
      <P>'By means of the People's Committee.'"</P>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
    <P>Pratchett's solutions tend to be autocratic, if variously benign and common-sensical.</P>
    <P>So, as story it bounces along; not the best Discworld novel, but worth it for it's moments. It's a shame that the McSweeney's aren't developed at all... a very old family, I didn't know Pratchett knew them... but then I suppose everybody does... "A very old established family".</P>
    <P ALIGN=RIGHT><B>S G Rayment</B></P>
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border2.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <A HREF="http://www.liberator.org.uk/cgi-bin/imagemap/imagemaps/buttons.map"><IMG SRC="../buttons.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#BUTTONS" ISMAP></A>
