  <!--Written by Rob Herbert-->
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 233 Reviews</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 233 Reviews</H1>
      <BR CLEAR=ALL><HR>
      <H2>The Daydreamer</H2>
      <H3>by Ian McEwan with illustrations by Anthony Browne<BR>Red Fox 1994 3.50</H3>
    </CENTER>
    <P>I didn't catch the name of my reviewer... "I've got that book" she said, "Daddy's reading it to me".  She liked the burglar most, her sister liked the baby. I liked William Cat.</P>
    <P>I've never really got on with Ian McEwan as an author; that level of sub-surreality doesn't quite gel for me. Neither I nor the bookshop where I acquired it identified it as a children's book at first, however for reading yourself pitched at around the ten year old I'd say. Useful for answering those difficult questions... the cat dies, the new baby arrives... wanking.</P>
    <P ALIGN=RIGHT><B>S G Rayment</B></P>
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border2.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <A HREF="http://www.liberator.org.uk/cgi-bin/imagemap/imagemaps/buttons.map"><IMG SRC="../buttons.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#BUTTONS" ISMAP></A>
