<HTML>
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 234 Reviews</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 234 Reviews</H1>
      <BR CLEAR=ALL><HR>
      <H2>The Lost World</H2>
      <H3>Michael Crichton<BR>Century, 1995, 15.99</H3>
    </CENTER>
    <P>Correctly sold as the successor to Jurassic Park, this continues the story of the disastrous genetically engineered theme park. The story of the failed contract has been suppressed with gagging contracts but there are stories of strange reptiles being sighted in Costa Rica, and a paleontologist follows clues that lead to an island off the central American coast, where he becomes marooned.</P>
    <P>A relief expedition sets out including Ian Malcolm and the mad mathematician who has survived a previous ordeal in Jurassic Park. Two children conveniently manage to stow away, providing scope for the book to be filmed as family entertainment.</P>
    <P>A commercial rival also seeks the secrets of the theme park,  and to steal some of the dinosaur eggs, with fatal consequences. Both groups end up on the island which has been the breeding laboratory for the theme park.</P>
    <P>It is as if the lost world has been created on the island of Dr Moreau. The narrative covers various theories of evolution and the mass extinction of the dinosaurs, and the island at first sight looks like offering some clues. The explorers soon find out though that he population is too large and that there must have been a unnaturally low life expectancy. The dinosaurs have been reared initially on sheep offal resulting in a form of mad cow disease.</P>
    <P>The book ends with no conclusion about the extinction and one character even queries scientific theory to an extent which would appeal to religious fundamentalists. The explorers manage to escape having decided that a future expedition will be necessary. The story is fairly gripping but it has nothing new to add to Jurassic Park, and the reader is left with the conclusion that the main reason for any future expedition is to provide Michael Crichton with a lucrative source of income.</P>
    <P ALIGN=RIGHT><B>Andrew Hudson</B></P>
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border2.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <A HREF="http://www.liberator.org.uk/cgi-bin/imagemap/imagemaps/buttons.map"><IMG SRC="../buttons.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#BUTTONS" ISMAP></A>
      <map name="BUTTONS">
