<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN//2.0">
<HTML>
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 234 Reviews</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 234 Reviews</H1>
      <BR CLEAR=ALL><HR>
      <H2>Ragged Schools, Ragged Children</H2>
      <H3>by Claire Seymour<BR>Ragged School Museum Trust 46-48 Copperfield Road, Stepney, London E3 4RR, 1995, 4.00</H3>
    </CENTER>
    <P>George Cruikshank's illustration on the cover says it all really. A dilapidated room, over-crowded with ramshackle children; some trying to learn, others trying but giving up, still more fighting, whilst a couple of toffs strain to keep on top of all this and impart some wisdom.</P>
    <P>The Ragged Schools were the sink schools of their day, from Robert Raikes' Sunday Schools of 1783 through to the end of the next century. The Forster Education Act and its successors were their undoing as they inevitably lacked the resources to keep pace with demands for higher standards, but survived awhile for the very destitute and no doubt the very disorderly.</P>
    <P>Seymour is mercifully unsanctimonious about Barnardo and his ilke. I regret that worthy though he may be, this part of the National Myth was delivered at least once a year throughout most of my school days. The effect of  getting the children some education, shelter and welfare is laudable, but one wonders about the intent - social control through religion.</P>
    <P>A good little book, and a good little museum. Since it is run largely by volunteers opening hours are few (tel. 0181-980-6405), but for any teachers struggling to meet the National Curriculum they run excellent Victorian classes.</P>
    <P ALIGN=RIGHT><B>S G Rayment</B></P>
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border2.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <A HREF="http://www.liberator.org.uk/cgi-bin/imagemap/imagemaps/buttons.map"><IMG SRC="../buttons.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#BUTTONS" ISMAP></A>
      <map name="BUTTONS">
        <area shape="polygon" alt="Home Page" coords="32,2,4,23,1,56,85,56,81,25,56,22,33,2,33,3" href="http://www.liberator.org.uk/index.htm">
        <area shape="polygon" alt="The Collective" coords="88,40,91,59,138,59,144,47,118,1,101,0,96,39,89,39" href="http://www.liberator.org.uk/Collective/Collective.html">
        <area shape="polygon" alt="Read Liberator" coords="151,41,148,56,218,55,207,45,214,29,195,22,196,2,165,0,153,40" href="http://www.liberator.org.uk/read.htm">
        <area shape="polygon" alt="Write for Liberator" coords="224,56,273,57,273,8,253,0,229,3,219,31,223,49" href="http://www.liberator.org.uk/write.htm">
        <area shape="polygon" alt="Subscribe" coords="288,57,360,42,371,26,344,0,305,4,278,38" href="http://www.liberator.org.uk/subs.htm">
        <area shape="default" nohref>
      </map>
    </CENTER>
  </BODY>
