<HTML>
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 234 Reviews</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 234 Reviews</H1>
      <BR CLEAR=ALL><HR>
      <H2>High Life in Verdopolis</H2>
      <H3>by Charlotte Bronte<BR>The British Library 1995</H3>
    </CENTER>
    <P>Written at the age of seventeen, this piece of ephemera, generously released by the British Library after 161 years, would be of little interest were it not for the author's subsequent reputation. As it is, part of the Glass Town saga of the precocious Bronte childhood, it is a fascinating precursor of things to come.</P>
    <P>Beyond this, it is a mirror of the impact of Romanticism and current events on the young mind. Despite the sway of Byron and his implicit radicalism, Bronte's hero worship ultimately draws her to the more dominant conservative elements of both. Within the book the tensions between the balance of compassion between Liberalism and Conservatism rage.</P>
    <P>It remains a work for the enthusiast, the literary detective or the lover of fine books. Illustrated with works by the author. Both attractive and charming.</P>
    <P ALIGN=RIGHT><B>S G Rayment</B></P>
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border2.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <A HREF="http://www.liberator.org.uk/cgi-bin/imagemap/imagemaps/buttons.map"><IMG SRC="../buttons.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#BUTTONS" ISMAP></A>
      <map name="BUTTONS">
        <area shape="polygon" alt="Home Page" coords="32,2,4,23,1,56,85,56,81,25,56,22,33,2,33,3" href="http://www.liberator.org.uk/index.htm">
