  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 234 Reviews</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 234 Reviews</H1>
      <BR CLEAR=ALL><HR>
      <H2>Seven</H2>
      <H3>(Director David Fincher Cert 18)</H3>
    </CENTER>
    <P>This is a film with some style, right from the uniquely designed credits. Morgan Freeman and Brad Pitt are reluctantly teamed up as a pair of detectives trying to trace a serial killer with a bizarre philosophical bent. The detectives' task is to make the connection behind a series of killings where the victims are apparently guilty of one of the seven deadly sins. The sub plot revolves around Freeman's bleak view of New York city life and his longed for imminent retirement to a log cabin; the fear of the city expressed by Pitt's wife (played by Gwyneth Paltrow); and the simplistic pursuit of justice from Pitt, the typically 90's angry young man.</P>
    <P>The visual device of darkness in so many of the scenes is effective, requiring more than the usual suspension of belief. But this is a modern film with style, sensitivity, and a brooding sense of violence, which is only gruesome in its after effects rather than from its on screen portrayal. Building to a logical but blinding climax this is the best American thriller on screen for some time. Watch out for the OSCAR nominations.</P>
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border2.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <A HREF="http://www.liberator.org.uk/cgi-bin/imagemap/imagemaps/buttons.map"><IMG SRC="../buttons.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#BUTTONS" ISMAP></A>
