<HTML>
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 234 Reviews</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 234 Reviews</H1>
      <BR CLEAR=ALL><HR>
      <H2>Heavy</H2>
      <H3>(Director James Mangold Cert 15)</H3>
    </CENTER>
    <P>This is a small, slow-moving film of closely observed emotions set in a run down small town American diner. A  lonely hopelessness pervades the life of all the characters but especially the central protagonist Victor (played brilliantly by Pruitt Taylor Vince); a fat, shy 30-something, who is the diner's chef living in the shadow of his dominating mother. An anti-hero of few words he communicates mostly from almost imperceptible nods of the head, but it his coping with his late awakening to women and the loss of his mother which is the film's central character study.</P>
    <P>An effective sound track, with original music from Thurston Moore, adds to the gloom and a sense of foreboding. However the film has a gently portrayed upbeat ending which in its way completes the coming of age of Victor. Co-starring Shelley Winters, Deborah Harry and newcomer Liv Tyler, the supporting cast provide sympathetic and natural performances.</P>
    <P>Heavy will not attract those moviegoers who want to see some action for their cinema entry fee. But for those who have the time to use the contemplative mood of the piece to reflect on the simple messages of the film, its worth an afternoon's visit.</P>
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border2.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <A HREF="http://www.liberator.org.uk/cgi-bin/imagemap/imagemaps/buttons.map"><IMG SRC="../buttons.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#BUTTONS" ISMAP></A>
      <map name="BUTTONS">
        <area shape="polygon" alt="Home Page" coords="32,2,4,23,1,56,85,56,81,25,56,22,33,2,33,3" href="http://www.liberator.org.uk/index.htm">
