<HTML>
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 234 Reviews</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 234 Reviews</H1>
      <BR CLEAR=ALL><HR>
      <H2>Land and Freedom</H2>
      <H3>(Director Ken Loach Cert 15)</H3>
    </CENTER>
    <P>I have never truly understood what the Spanish Civil War was about and the underlying reasons why Franco won, and anyone else admitting to the same level of ignorance could do worse than take a look at this. Ken Loach managed to attract an impressive array of backers from various European sources to make the film, which just goes to show that one can make historical dramas, with extras and battle scenes, without relying on the resources of Hollywood.</P>
    <P>Whilst it is an ambitiously bigger canvas than is usual for this director, there are still the tell tale signs that this is unquestionably a Ken Loach film, and that Ken Loach is uncompromisingly a socialist. The story is told in flashback from modern times as a grand daughter discovers her grandfather's mementos of the Civil War period after his death.</P>
    <P>The film effectively conveys the monotony of the war from the view of the trenches although does not question the need for it. A typically Loach scene is the staged debate between the conquering heroes of a people's militia, and the local villagers after their liberation from Franco's forces. Focusing on the difference between a possible collectivisation of the village lands and the division of the landowner's estate between the villagers, it demonstrates in minutiae the fatal flaw in the approach of the anti-Franco forces. With different agendas and definitions of socialism the coalition is bound to collapse. And so it proves as the tale unwinds. This is not a film for the faint-hearted, as there are some truly violent and emotional moments, and the optimism portrayed in the final scenes is painfully naive. Nevertheless this is well made, and recommended viewing.</P>
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border2.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <A HREF="http://www.liberator.org.uk/cgi-bin/imagemap/imagemaps/buttons.map"><IMG SRC="../buttons.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#BUTTONS" ISMAP></A>
      <map name="BUTTONS">
        <area shape="polygon" alt="Home Page" coords="32,2,4,23,1,56,85,56,81,25,56,22,33,2,33,3" href="http://www.liberator.org.uk/index.htm">
