<HTML>
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 235 Reviews</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 235 Reviews</H1>
      <BR CLEAR=ALL><HR>
      <H2>Heat</H2>
      <H3>(Dir Michael Mann Cert 15)</H3>
    </CENTER>
    <P>This is a crime thriller which reaches a standard rarely achieved by others. The two protagonists, Al Pacino and Robert De Niro play their parts in a chilling but largely predictable cat and mouse story. The detective (Pacino) has the typical policeman's failing third marriage and a disturbed step-daughter for additional emotional trauma. The big time crook (De Niro) is the cold and calculating emotional island who believes that anyone in his profession has to be prepared, if necessary, to walk out on any relationship within thirty seconds to guarantee survival.</P>
    <P>As is usual in this kind of movie the viewer gets a number of human interest subplots relating to the supporting cast which reflect the themes of the main storyline. And true to the genre we have the predictable final shoot out between the two principals at the end. So what makes it so good?</P>
    <P>It is because the central performances of Pacino and De Niro are superb. And they are at their best in a wryly comic scene when they confront each other over a coffee to discuss the possible outcome of the tale. (There is also an impeccable performance from Jon Voight playing the aging criminal Mr Fixit behind the scenes.)</P>
    <P>Despite the surprisingly mild 15 certificate the onscreen violence is realistic and therefore horrific as a consequence. To get the full effect a front row seat in a cinema with a Dolby stereo sound system will do the trick!</P>
    <P>But be warned, this is not a film for the faint hearted or one with sensitive hearing. But if you do like American crime thrillers then this is the best for some time.</P>
    <P ALIGN=RIGHT><B>William Tranby</B></P>
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border2.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <A HREF="http://www.liberator.org.uk/cgi-bin/imagemap/imagemaps/buttons.map"><IMG SRC="../buttons.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#BUTTONS" ISMAP></A>
