<HTML>
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Liberator: Issue 236 Reviews</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrnd.jpg">
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../read.gif">
      <H1><IMG SRC="../lib_on.gif"><BR>Issue 236 Reviews</H1>
      <BR CLEAR=ALL><HR>
      <H2>Swimming with Sharks</H2>
      <H3>(Dir George Huang, Cert 15)</H3>
    </CENTER>
    <P>This is a gem of a film, which probably won't get the exposure it deserves. It is a spiteful portrayal of all that is bad about the Hollywood movie business. Kevin Spacey plays the part of the Senior Vice President of production at a major film studio who hires a new personal assistant played by the fresh faced and apparently principled Frank  Whaley. Spacey is still on his way to the top job and is unscrupulous in his approach.</P>
    <P>The female film producer who befriends young Whaley (Michelle Forbes) is also hawking a film project for studio support and so a question mark arises about her, and everyone else's motives. And that is most of the plot. But what we get for 90 minutes is a brilliant study in a tragicomic relationship between a tyrannical boss and long-suffering servant, and finally what happens when the worm turns.</P>
    <P>The film is related by a series of flashbacks and there is a superb twist to the finish. Kevin Spacey's masterful performance means he reaches our sympathies even after demonstrating the most complete portrayal of a manic bully seen on the screen for some time. This is definitely worth tracking down even if, ultimately, it can only be found at the video shop.</P>
	 <P ALIGN=RIGHT><B>William Tranby</B></P>
    <CENTER>
      <IMG SRC="../border2.gif"><BR CLEAR=ALL>
      <A HREF="http://www.liberator.org.uk/cgi-bin/imagemap/imagemaps/buttons.map"><IMG SRC="../buttons.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#BUTTONS" ISMAP></A>
      <map name="BUTTONS">
        <area shape="polygon" alt="Home Page" coords="32,2,4,23,1,56,85,56,81,25,56,22,33,2,33,3" href="http://www.liberator.org.uk/index.htm">
