alue in Society</h3><h4>|<a href="Day-in-History-Apr.html">This Day in History--April '96</a>|<a href="Day-in-History-May.html">This Day in History--May '96</a>|<br>| <a href="Current-Values-Mar.html">Values in Society--March '96</a> |<br></h4></center><hr noshade></b><center><h4>Nota Bene</h4></center><p>After reviewing the Table of Contents, I recommend that youread the <a href="#Pref">Preface</a> before reading otherdocuments.</p><hr noshade><ol>	<p>	<li> <a href="#ADOB">Adobe Acrobat Service Center.</a>	</p>		<p>	To provide information on downloading documents with all of	their original formatting, even though you may not have the	application in which the document was created.	</p>		<p>	<li> <a href="#BI">Bibliography </a>	</p>		<p>	<li> <a href="#BOO">Book Reviews</a>	</p>			<p>	<li> <a href="#BU">Business Department.</a>	</p>		<ul>		<p>		<li> <a href="#PG">Productivity Galore</a>		<li> <a href="#PF">Productivity FAQ</a>		<li> <a href="#BF">Business Financing</a>		</p>		</ul>	<li> <a href="#COMN">Comments on News Events</a>	<p>	Comments on true news events regarding the creation of	new and useful property which has the potential for enhancing	the quality of life on this planet.  These are  <b>normal</b>events	in the mainstream of history.	</p>	<li> <a href="#COMP">Comments on Press Articles</a>	<p>	Comments on press articles forconcerning political events involving	inteference in, and/or the destruction of property. These are	<b>average</b>, abnormal events,	outside of the mainstream of history, which do not enhance the	quality of life.	</p>	<p>	<li> <a href="#EVENTS">Database of Important Events in		History.</a>	</p>		<p>		A listing of events representing or resultin in the creation of		property, rather than the normal listing of events resulting		in the destruction of property.		</p>			<li> <a href="#PE">Database of Important People in		History.</a>				<p>		A Database containing only names of those who are		important in history.  Be sure to read the essay on		this subject before using the database.		</p>	<li> <a href="#DAY">(This) Day in History.</a>			<p>		A monthly listing of important events in history for each		day of the month, taken from the database of more than		3,000 important people and events in history.		</p>		<li><a href="Dumont.html">The Dumont Institute</a>		<p>	We have created a special section for the Dumont Institute for Public	Policy Research.  Among other things, they offer expert speakers on a	wide range of subjects illustrating the problems of political societies,	and related to creating and maintaining freedom.	</p>		<li> <a href="#ES">Essays.</a><ul>	<p>	<li><a href="#USC">The Universal Salvage Corporation</a> Essays	</p>		<p>		Tired of reading articles by politicians defending the		indefensible, as George Orwell said?  And with non-solutions		to the problems of society?  Read essays and articles that		trend toward the rational and moral, and which contain		real, permanent, moral solutions to today's problems.		</p>	<p>	<li><a href="#FFF">The Future of Freedom Foundation.</a> Essays	</p>			<p>		The articles in this section are published through the		courtesy of <cite>The Future of Freedom Foundation</cite>		and the individual authors.		</p>		<p>	<li><a href="#FEE">The Foundation for Economic Education.</a> Essays	</p>		<p>		The articles in this section are published through the		courtesy of <cite>The Foundation for Economic		Education</cite> and the individual authors.	</p>		<p>	<li><a href="#DI">Dumont Institute</a> Essays	</p>		<p>	In this section we publish essays provided by the Dumont Institute,	written primarily by Dr. Robert W. McGee.  For more information on	Dr. McGee and the essays, visit this section.	</p>			<li> <a href="#OTH">Other Essays on Freedom.</a>		<p>	Essays and articles  from individual authors, published at	their request and/or with their permission.	</p>	</ul>	<li> <a href="#SLEA">Sleaze</a>	<p>	The magazine of Politics	</p>	<li> <a href="#QUO">Quotations.</a>			<p>		The favorite quotations of the Administrator.		</p>	<p>	<li> <a href="#SUBSC">Subscriber Services.</a>	</p>	<li><a href="#VALUE">Value in Society</a>		<ul>		<p>		<li><a href="#HIST">Historial Sources of Value in Society.</a>		</p>				<p>		A table illustrating from where we have received value		in the past.		</p>				<p>		<li><a href="#CURR">Sources of Value in Current Society.</a>		</p>				<p>		A table illustrating from where we receive value in current		society.		</p>	</ul>		<li> <a href="#DE">Word Definitions.</a>			<p>		Word definitions which trend toward the succinct, true,		valid, and moral, and which can be used to build new and		useful knowledge in the societal sphere.		</p>			<li> <a href="#GL">Word & Concept Discussion</a>			<p>		While this contains many of the same words as the Word		Definition section, there are generally comments--sometimes		extensive--related to the definitions.		</p>			</ol><hr noshade><center>[<a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a>]</center><hr noshade><h3> <a name="ADOB"><a href="Adobe.html"> Adobe Acrobat	Service Center</a></h3>		<p>	For those wishing to download documents with all of their	original formatting, in addition to making essays available	in text format, we also make them available in Adobe Acrobat	format, and provide a facility for downloading the Free-of-Charge	Acrobat Reader from the Adobe Home Page.	</p><hr><h3><a name="BI"><a href="Books.html">Bibliography</a></h3><p>The bibliography lists books which, in general, contain more than theaverage amount of true and useful information.  There may occasionallybe a few books which are mostly negative, but sometimes it is necessaryto comprehend the negative as part of the solution to a problem.</p><p>As with all inputs, whether verbally or from reading, it is imcumbentonthe listener or reader to think and analyze what they read.  To thenlook atthe world around you for corroboration.  Until the speaker or writerhas avery high "corroboration factor" with you, you should neverautomaticallyaccept what a speaker says or a reader writes.  Even then, you shouldoccasionally make checks to verify they have not ventured into therealmof the fabulous.</p><hr><h3> <a name="BOO"><a href="Book-Reviews.html">Book	Reviews</a></h3>		<p>	Review of books, good and bad.	</p><hr><h3><a name="BU">Business Department</h3>	<p>	The "Productivity Galore" and "FAQ" sections provide the solution	for the current, basic problems of the business world.	</p><ul>	<li><a href="Business-Essays.html">Business Essays</a>.		<p>	Various essays on business, presented by The Universal Salvage	Corporation.	</p>				<li><h4><a name="PG">Productivity Galore</a></h4>		<p>	A clear exposition of what is wrong with current methods of	production compensation.  This essay, which is quite long, provides	the solution to the business problems of low productivity,	lack-lustre innovation, and variable quality.  The FAQ should be	read in confunction with this essay.	</p>		<p>	<a href="PG.html">Productivity Galore Business Modules</a>	</p>		<li><h4><a name="PF"><a href="Productivity.html">Productivity		FAQ</a></h4>		<p>	Record of an interview on the subject of <cite>Productivity	Galore.</cite>	</p>		<li><h4><a name="BF">Business Financing</a></h4>		<p>	This module illustrates the method of the future for financing	new products or companies.  A system which maximized the return	to the investor, shields the investor from non-business events, and	provides a system in which the founder never loses control of the	company or product.	</p>		<p>	Not yet available on the server.	</p></ul><hr><h3> <a name="COMN"><a href="News-Articles-Mar.html">Comments	on News Articles</a> for March</h3>	<p>	"News" of course implies that there is something new.	Such as the creation of new and better products, and new	ideas that have the potential for improving the quality of	life.  A potential which is still-born in the <i>miasma</i> of a	world of societal structures based on coercion.	</p>		<p>	This section should contain no information involving political	activities and the associated property interference, and	will be a real pleasure to work on, since it	will deal with people who are important and significant	in history.	</p>	<hr><h3> <a name="COMP"><a href="Press-Articles.html">Comments	on Press Articles</a></h3>	<p>	This section will include comments on continuing	property interference by the politicians, and the attendant	assault by politicians on the quality of life.  This can not be	termed as "news," since it does not involve anything new.	This has been going on for millions of years, and is only	getting worse.	</p>		<p>	The discussions in this section will help you to understand	what is really going on in the world, and the consequences	for the survival of the specie.  This will be a depressing	section to work on, since it will be dealing with people and	events of no significance or importance in history.	</p><hr><h3><a name="EVENTS">Database of Important Events in	History</a></h3>		<p>	Based on the correct concept of importance, this database lists	events in history which are important, and therefore moral.	Generally, they represent events which increase, or have the	potential for increasing our knowledge of our universe.	</p>		<p>	The exception to the above is when they chronicle certain aspects	or events of the life of important people which are of interest.	</p>		<p>	Existing, but not yet available on the server.	</p><hr><h3><a name="PE">Database of Important People</a></h3>	<p>	Based on the correct concept of importance, this database lists	people who have been important in history, or who are importantnow,	although it tends to emphasize people from history as opposed to	people from recent or current time.	</p>		<p>	I do <b>not</b> claim that all important people are listed herein,	but I do claim that people who are listed are in fact important in	the correct sense of the word.  It therefore contains virtually	no people from the political world--perhaps only four or five	in all of history.  And they are there despite their occupation,	rather than because of it.	</p>		<p>	Existing, but not yet available on the server.	</p><hr><h3><a name="DAY">This Day in History</a></h3>	<p>	Almost without exception, newspaper columns with this title	list events of property destruction or the birth or death of	unimportant people in history.  Such as politicians, whether of	the civil, military, or religious branch.	</p>		<p>	This section list the birth of important people and important	events in history related to the creation of property of all types.	It also lists people who entertain and bring humor and beauty to our	lives.	</p><ul>				<h4>This Day in History for <a href="Day-in-History-Feb.html">		February</a></h4>	<h4>This Day in History for <a href="Day-in-History-Mar.html">		March</a></h4>	</ul><hr noshade><center>[<a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a>]</center><hr noshade><h3><a name="ES"><a href="Essays.html">Essays</a></h3><ul>	<h4><a name="DI">Dumont Institute for Public Policy Research</a></h4>		<p>	Visit the Dumont Institute for Public Policy Research section to	locate expert speakers on many subjects  and read essays from various	authors associated with the Institute.	</p>		<p>	Their journal, <i>The Journal of Accounting, Ethics &amp; Public 	Policy</i> is also looking for suitable papers.  You may find out more	about this by visiting the <a href="Dumont-Home.html">Dumont	Institute</a> section.	</p>		<h4><a name="USC">Universal Salvage Corporation essays</a></h4>	<p>	Essays with important concepts and tools which can be	used to build a rational and durable society whose	time-scale of existence will be concomitant with that	of our local universe.	</p>		<p>	Visit <a href="Essays.html">The Essay Pages of The	Freedom Server </a> to read our own essays.	</p>	<h4><a name="FFF">Future of Freedom Foundation essays</a></h4>	<p>	The articles in this section are published through the	courtesy of <cite>The Future of Freedom Foundation</cite> and the	individual authors.	</p>		<p>	Visit the <a href="Future-of-Freedom.html"> Future of Freedom	Foundation </a> essay pages to read some of these fine essays.	</p>	<h4><a name="FEE">Foundation for Economic Education	essays.</a></h4>	<p>	The articles in this section are published through the	courtesy of <cite>The Foundation for Economic Education</cite>	and the individual authors.	</p>		<p>	Visit the <a href="Economic-Education.html">Foundation for	Economic Education </a> pages to read some of the fine essays	from this organization.	</p>		<h4><a name="OTH">Other Essays on Freedom.</a></h4>		<p>	These essays add to our knowledge by illustrating the problems	with our current societal structures based on coercion and	provide pointers to the solution.	</p>		<p>	Visit the <a href="Other-Essays.html">Other Essays on	Freedom.</a> pages to read some very thought-provoking and	important essays.	</p></ul><hr><h3><a name="Pref">Preface</a></h3>	<p>	You can either read the Preface in <a href="Preface.html">HTML</a>	format, or,	</p>		<p>	you can download it in <a href="Preface.pdf">Adobe	Acrobat</a> format.  Document size 18 Kb.<hr><h3> <a name="SLEA"><a href="Sleaze.html">Sleaze</a></h3>	<p>	This publication covers all branches of politics: Civil, Military,and	Religious.	</p>		<p>	Read <b>Sleaze</b> for <a href="Sleaze-Mar.html">March</a>.	</p><hr><h3><a name="QUO"><a href="Quotations.html">Quotations</a></h3>	<p>	It should go without saying that these are among my favorite	<a href="Quotations.html">Quotations</a>.  With a few exceptions I have	chosen 	them 	because 	they are true and especially important as in input into the	construction of a rational and durable society.	</p>		<p>	There are a few which are also humorous, and at first thought	might seem to be frivolous, but even they have a very important	message.	<p><hr><h3><a name="SUBSC"><a href="Subscriber.html">Subscriber	Services</a></h3>	<p>	Subscribing to the essays of <cite>The Freedom	Server</cite>&copy; will have a number of advantages.	</p><hr><h3><a name="VALUE">Value in Society.<a/></h3><ul>	<p>	These complementary sections illustrate from where it is we	as individuals receive value in society.	</p>		<h4><a name="HIST">Historical Value in Society.</a></h4>		<p>	Using events from history, we contrast acts of property creation	and those of property interference and destruction (political	acts and events) showing which concept and individuals have	provided us--and continue to provide us--with value in the	sense of an enhanced quality of life.	</p>		<p>	Still under construction.	</p>		<h4><a name="CURR">Sources of Value in Current Society.</a></h4>		<p>	Using current events, we contrast acts of property creation	and those of property interference and destruction (political	acts and events) showing which concept and individuals have	provided us--and continue to provide us--with value in the	sense of an enhanced quality of life.	</p>		<p>	<h5>Value in Current Society for 1996 <a href="Current	Values-Mar.html"> March</a></h5>	</p>		</ul><hr><h3><a name="DE"><a href="Words.html">Word Definitions</a></h3>	<p>	Precise and absolute definitions for words commonly used in the	"social" sphere, as opposed to the commonly used definitions, which	are imprecise and vary depending on "circumstances."	</p>		<p>	Precise, absolute definitions are necessary to build a body ofuseful	knowledge, and to create additional new and useful knowledge.	</p><hr><h3><a name="GL"><a href="Glossary.html">Word &amp; Concept	Discussion</a></h3>	<p>	As opposed to the "Definitions" section, this section provides a	discussion on many commonly used words and phrases.	</p><hr noshade><center>[<a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a>]</center><hr noshade><center>&copy: 1995 - The Universal Salvage Corporation<p><i>Specialists in Dying Civilizations</i></p></center><hr><b>Contact Information:</b><br><tt>E-Mail: administrator@Freedom-Server.co.uk<br></tt><hr noshade><hr><p>The URL of this page is:</p><CENTER>&lt;http://www.freedom-server.co.uk/Contents.html&gt; </CENTER><HR NOSHADE></BODY></HTML>
