<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>The Freedom Server - Sleaze, Magazine of Politics</TITLE>        	<META Name="Author" CONTENT="William W. Morgan">		<META Name="Keys"		CONTENT="Galambos,government,coercion,capitalism,			history,Bedeman,politics,corruption,bribery">			<META HTTP-EQUIV="Reply-to"		CONTENT="administrator@freedom-server.co.uk">    </HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#fdfaff"><CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H1>The Freedom Server<sup>&copy;</sup></H1><H3>Second Edition</H3><HR noshade><H2>Sleaze</H2><H3>The Magazine of Politics.</H3><hr noshade><p>This page has been visited</p><IMG SRC="/cgi-bin/Counter.cgi?www.freedom-server.co.uk.Sleaze-Mar.html" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> <p>since 1996, May 4.</p></CENTER><hr noshade>Created: 1995, August 1<BR>Revised: 1996, July 7<BR>Version: 002k<HR><CENTER><H4>| <A HREF="index.html">Home</A> | <A HREF="Contents.html">Table of Contents</A> |</H4></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><p>Your politicians--and the hard-earned money they have taken from you--inaction.</p><p>This publication covers all departments of politics: Civil, Military, andReligious.</p><p>The main objective of aspiring politicians is to get elected. Then, onceelected and having descended* to political office, the main objective isto be re-elected. To ensure achieving this objective, they will do virtuallyanything, as illustrated in this section.</p><UL><p>* Descending to political office <B>is</B> the correct direction, sincevirtually all political activites are immoral.(See the <A HREF="Glossary.html">Glossary of Terms</A> fordefinitions).</p><p>A politician can only be said to have &quot;ascended&quot; to a positionwhen they are no longer in a position to control the property and livesof others without the consent of the victim(s).</p></UL><p>Trading people, places, and things for votes. Their main objective is toremain in power--in control of other people's lives and money. The exhilarationof people kowtowing to you, and the knowledge that others are looking enviouslyat this process. The endless &quot;photo opportunities&quot; to enhanceone's position of power. The arriving, waiting, and departing limousines.The helicopters to make sure one is not caught in the traffic lesser mortalsare subject to, and which the politicians are unable to solve. (A dilutedand imparied form of socialist-capitalism is able to build more cars thanpoliticians can provide roads for.)</p><p>It is not so much the &quot;sleaze&quot; of politics that is significant,but rather the emptiness of the concept of one person or group of personscontrolling the lives and destiny of others through the mechanism of coercion.Even in the so-called &quot;democratic&quot; societies in which people supposedlygive their consent to this coercive process. Mainly, I believe, because&quot;it has always been this way,&quot; and because there seems not otherway for volitional societies to operate, which is of course not true.</p><p>Such coercive systems violate a basic law of nature regarding the behaviorof volitional beings which states that all concepts of happiness pursuedby <B>moral</B> means are equally valid. A corollary might be that any attemptby one individual to interfere in this process and the life of another personis of course immoral, and it should be obvious that it is counter-productiveand leads to disorder in a society.</p><p>Do you want someone else's idea of happiness substituted for yours? Do youwant their idea of happiness imposed on you? Is it realistic that groupsof people should have the same idea or concept imposed upon them? Forgettingfor the moment that such a thing is in any case immoral.</p><p>The word "sleaze" is often used to indicate corruption. But itshould be remembered that corruption can not exist unless one party to arelationship has an accepted and "authorized" ("legal," in politicalsocieties) ability to control the lives and properties of others withouttheir permission. Without this access to the monopoly on police powers whicha political state encompasses the concept of corruption loses all itsmeaning.</p><BR><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H3>Sleaze</H3></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><table border>	<TR> 		<TH>Information Source</TH>		<TH>Political Action or Event</TH>		<TH>Translation/Reality/Comment</TH>	</TR>		<TR>		<TD><B>Sunday Times (London)</B><BR>			1996, March 3<BR>			"Clinton declares emergency over anti-Cuba protest"<BR>			p. 1-18 </TD>						<TD>			<p>			The "Commander in Chief" and Chief Draft			Dodger has declared a "National Emergency" over Cuba's			shooting down of two US private aircraft.			</p>						<p>			He is also proposing a new law regarding property			expropriated by Castro after his rebellion against the			previous Ruler, Battista. This law will have disastrous			consequences for US and British companies doing business			in Cuba.			</p>			<p>			However, the American Ruler--Clinton--has the authority			to delay implementation of the law for six months, which			he will do so as to be able to obtain the vote of			Cuban-Americans in Florida. This being crucial to his			re-election.			</p>			</TD>						<TD>			<p>			Is this, or is this not a bribe?			</p>			<p>			Of course it is, but not if you are spart of the Political			R&eacute;gime, where it is only considered "politics"			</p>			</TD>		</TR>				<TR>			<TD><B>Newsweek</B><br>				1996, June 3<br>				"Dulling a Sharp Wedge"<br>				p. 22			</TD>						<TD>Dole announces his support for a "bill" outlawing gay				marriage.  Clinton announces he is also for such a				decree.</TD>						<TD>				<p>				Dole does this because it is felt that the majority of				those who will cast political votes are also against				such marriages, and thus he will gain votes, with the				possibility of descending to the presidency.				</p>								<p>				Clinton must announce the same position, whether or				not he believes in it, so that he does not run the risk				of losing votes, as thus his position as the				<b>F&uuml;hrer</b> or "leader" of the American				political r&eacute;gime.				</p>								<p>				This of course is a standard type of political bribe,				bribes being acceptable and "legal" in politics.  But				it goes deeper than just bribery, which of course is				not acceptable outside of politics.				</p>								<p>				The reality is that <b>F&uuml;hrer Clinton</b> (why not				use the German word for "leader," which is what he				proclaims to be?) is <b>not</b> against gay				marriages, but rather is <b>for</b> them.  So, in				addition to a <b>bribe</b>, there is also <b>fraud</b>.				Fraud is also something which is allowed in politics				when you are part of the r&eacute;gime, but not when				you outside of the Ruling Party Circle.				</p>								<p>				Score: Politics One (1), the specie zero (0).  And the				"game" continues....				</p>								<p>				A :"bill" is of course is the new euphemism for what in				centuries-past would have been called an "Imperial				Decree."				</TD>		</TR>				<TR>			<TD><B>The Sunday Times</B><BR>				1996, July 7<BR>				"Laying down the law on order"<BR>				p. 3-7			</TD>						<TD> 			<p>			Mr. Jack Shaw, the "Shadow" Police &amp; Security			Minister, although they use the emphemism of "Home			Minister, is proposing to get tough with criminals.			</p>						<p>			According to the author, Chrissy Iley, Mr. Shaw proposes			to "... protect those who do not want seek his protection			as well as those who do."  It is also noted that he ".. wants			to 'out-tough' Michael Howard," [the current Police and			Security Czar].			</p>			</TD>			<TD>			<p>Typical of all politicians, he assumes who knows better			than those "destined be ruled" by "those destined to the			rulers," and wish to get into a position in which he can			exert the maximum of interference in the property and lives			of others.			</p>						<p>			As such, this qualifies him as a person of high negative			importance in history, and certain to go down in history,			which is the correct direction for all such people.			</p>						<p>			And, typical of all politicians out of power, his main			function and purpose in life is to criticize those in power			as a means of ursurping their position.  And, as with all			critics, he has not real solution to anything.			</p>			 </TD>		</TR>				<TR>			<TD><B>Publication</B><BR>				Date<BR>				Title<BR>				p. nn			</TD>						<TD> Politics</TD>			<TD> Reality </TD>		</TR></table> <table border>	<TR>		<TH>Information Source</TH>		<TH>Political Action or Event</TH>		<TH>Translation/Reality/Comment</TH>	</TR>		<TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>			Date<BR>			Title<BR>			p. nn		</TD>				<TD> Politics</TD>		<TD> Reality </TD>	</TR>		<TR>		<TD><B>Publication</B><BR>			Date<BR>			Title<BR>			p. nn		</TD>				<TD> Politics</TD>		<TD> Reality</TD>			</TR><HR NOSHADE><CENTER>[<A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A>]</CENTER><HR NOSHADE>	<TR>		<TD><B>Publication</B><BR>			Date<BR>			Title<BR>			p. nn		</TD>				<TD> Politics</TD>		<TD> Reality </TD>	</TR>		<TR>		<TD><B>Publication</B><BR>			Date<BR>			Title<BR>			p. nn		</TD>				<TD> Politics</TD>		<TD Reality</td>	</TR></TABLE><HR NOSHADE><CENTER>[<A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A>]</CENTER><HR NOSHADE><table border>	<TR>		<TH>Information Source</TH>		<TH>Political Action or Event</TH>		<TH>Translation/Reality/Comment</TH>	</TR>		<TR>		<TD><B>Publication</B><BR>			Date<BR>			Title<BR>			p. nn		</TD>				<TD> Politics</TD>		<TD> Reality</TD>	</TR>		<TR>		<TD><B>Publication</B><BR>			Date<BR>			Title<BR>			p. nn		</TD>				<TD> Politics</TD>		<TD> Reality</TD>	</TR>		<TR>		<TD><B>Publication</B><BR>			Date<BR>			Title<BR>			p. nn		</TD>				<TD> Politics</TD>		<TD>Reali