tion speakers bureau.</P>		<P>	<B>Houston Says No to Zoning</B>	</p>		<[>	<A HREF="Individual-Rights.pdf">Adobe	Acrobat</A> Format, 28 Kb file.	</P>		<P>	<A HREF="Individual-Rights.html">HTML</A> Format	</P>	</UL><HR><LI> <A NAME="MKTS"><B>Free Markets and Externalities: The	Symmetry of Unintended Effects</B></A><UL><P>Environment ideology and regulation often overlook the beneficialeffects of industrial activities.</P><P>by James Rolph Edwards</P><P>James Rolf Edwards is Associated Professor of Economics atMontana State University-Northern.</P>	<P>	<B>Free Markets and Externalities: The	Symmetry of Unintended Effects</B>	</p>		<p>	<A HREF="Free-Markets.pdf">Adobe	Acrobat</A> Format, 28 Kb file.	</P>		<P>	<A HREF="Free-Markets.html">HTML</A> Format	</P>	</UL><HR><LI> <A NAME="INFO"><B>One Information Superhighway:	Take It or Leave It?</B></A><UL><P>The dangers of centralized control of information networks.</P><P>by Eric-Charles Banfield</P><P>Mr. Banfield is owner of Banfield Analytical Services in Westmont,Ilinois, specializing in writing, speaking, and analysis of financial,economic, and public-policy issues.</P>		<P>	<B>One Information Superhighway: Take It or Leave It?</B>	</p>		<p>	<A HREF="Info-Superhighway.pdf">Adobe	Acrobat</A> Format, 11 Kb file.	</P>		<P>	<A HREF="Info-Superhighway.html">HTML</A> Format	</P>	</UL><HR><LI> <A NAME="SF"><B>Seizure Fever: The War on Property Rights</B></A><UL><P>The dangers of centralized control of information networks.</P><P>by James Bovard</P><P>Mr. Bovard is author of Shakedown: How the Government Screws You fromA to Z (Viking, 1995); 132 pages; $14.95, and Lost Rights: The Destructionof American Liberty (St. Martin's, 1994).</P><P>You may read the review of <A HREF="Book-Reviews.html#SD">Shakedown</A> in the Book Review section.</P><P>This essay is considered to be extremely important, showing the levelto which the American political r&eacute;gime has sunk, using tacticssimilar to the Gestapo in Hitler's Germany.</P><P>This includes people spying on their fellow citizens and reporting<B>suspicions</B> and <B>hearsay</B> to the political police, whether itbe the FBI, DEA, or some other branch.  And, as the essay pounts out, itis often done for reasons of revenge against people who are innocent ofany crime, but have their property confiscated from them without thecherished "due process."</P>	<P>		<B> Seizure Fever: The War on Property Rights</B>	</p>		<p>	<A HREF="Property-Seizure-Rights.txt">Text</A> Format, 11 Kb	file.	</P>		<P>	<A HREF="Property-Seizure-Rights.pdf">Adobe	Acrobat</A> Format, 11 Kb file.	</P>		<p>	<A HREF="Property-Seizure-Rights.html">HTML</A> Format	</P>	</UL><HR NOSHADE><CENTER>[<A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A>]</CENTER><HR NOSHADE><LI> <A NAME="ANTI"><B>The Failure of Antitrust Policy</B></A><UL><P>This article discusses how political state regulation designed to helpconsumers actually hurts them.  As does all political state interferencein the free market process.</P><P>by D. T. Armentano</P><P>Dr. Armentano is professor of economics at the University of Hartford,and the author of "Antitrust and Monopoly," Second Edition (New York,Holmes &amp; Meier, 1990).</P>		<P>	<B>The Failure of Antitrust Policy</B>	</p>		<p>	<A HREF="Antitrust-Policy-Failure.pdf">Adobe	Acrobat</A> Format, 18 Kb file.	</P>		<P>	<A HREF="Antitrust-Policy-Failure.html">HTML</A> Format	</P></UL><HR><LI> <A NAME="SOME"><B>Some International Neglect Would Be Good	for Africa.</B></A><UL><P>This essay discusses how "helping" areas such as Africa makes themdependent on the aid, and creates a situation in which they end upwith no incentive to take care of themselves. As with all attempts atwelfare...</P><P>by James C. W. Ahiakpor</P><P>Dr. Ahiakpor, who was born in Ghana, West Africa, is Professor andChairman of the Department of Economics, California StateUniversity, Hayward.</P>		<P>	<B>Some International Neglect Would Be Good	for Africa.</B>	</p>		<p>	<A HREF="Africa-and-Neglect.pdf">Adobe	Acrobat</A> Format, 21 Kb file.	</P>		<P>	<A HREF="Africa-and-Neglect.html">HTML</A> Format.	</P></UL><HR><LI> <A NAME="PROP"><B>Property Rights, American Constitutionalism,and International Human Rights "Law."</B></A><UL><P>This essay discusses how the actions of American politicians, who donot understand the concept of individual property, are thereforeincapable of comprehending a true sense of human rights.</P><P>by Daniel F. Walker</P><P>Mr. Walker is an attorney in private practice in Tallahassee, Florida.</P>	<P>		<B>Property Rights, American Constitutionalism,	and International Human Rights "Law."</B>	</p>	<P>	<A HREF="Property-Human-Rights.pdf">Adobe	Acrobat</A> Format, 21 Kb file.	</P>		<p>	<A HREF="Property-Human-Rights.html">HTML</A> Format	</P>	</UL><HR><LI> <A NAME="RIGH"><B>Rights vs. Entitlements</B></A><UL><P>The title says it all; when people are provided with "entitlements," theysoon begin to believe they are truly "entitled" to them, and that it istheir "right" to have them.</P><P>by Steven Yates</P><P>Dr. Yates is a Visiting Assistant Professor, Department of Philosophy,University of South Carolina, Academic Year 1993-94; Salvatori Fellow,The Heritage Foundation, 1992-94, and author of Civil Wrongs: What WentWrong With Affirmative Action (San Francisco: ICS Press, 1994) andrecent articles and reviews in Public Affairs Quarterly, SocialSciences Quarterly, Reason Papers, IPI Insights, and other periodicals </P>	<P>		<B>Rights vs. Entitlements</B>	</p>		<p>	<A HREF="Rights-vs-Entitlements.txt">Text</A> Format, 11 Kb	file.	</P>		<P>	<A HREF="Rights-vs-Entitlements.pdf">Adobe	Acrobat</A> Format, 14 Kb file.	</P>		<p>	<A HREF="Rights-vs-Entitlements.html">HTML</A> Format	</P>	</UL><HR NOSHADE><CENTER>[<A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A>]</CENTER><HR NOSHADE><CENTER>&copy: 1995 - The Universal Salvage Corporation<P><I>Specialists in Dying Civilizations</I></P></CENTER><HR><B>Contact Information:</B><BR><TT>E-Mail: administrator@Freedom-Server.co.uk<BR></TT><P>The URL of this page is:</P><CENTER>&lt;http://www.freedom-server.co.uk/Economic-Education.html&gt;</CENTER><HR NOSHADE></BODY></HTML>
