<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>The Freedom Server - Word &amp; Concept Discussion</TITLE>        <META Name="AU" CONTENT="William W. Morgan">        <META HTTP-EQUIV="KEYWORDS"		CONTENT="Galambos, definitions, dictionary, government, 		coercion, capitalism, Bedeman, justice, truth, rationality,		history, epistemology">			<META HTTP-EQUIV="Reply-to"		CONTENT="administrator@freedom-server.co.uk">    </HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"></HEAD><BODY><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H1>The Freedom Server<sup>&copy;</sup></H1><H3>Second Edition</H3></CENTER><hr noshade><p>This page has been visited </p><center><p><IMG SRC="/cgi-bin/Counter.cgi?www.freedom-server.co.uk.Glossary.html" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> </p><p>since 1996, March 16th, although it was created on1995, August 1. </p><HR NOSHADE><H2>Word &amp; Concept Discussion</H2><H4>| <A HREF="Index.html">Home </A>| <A HREF="Contents.html">Table of Contents </A>| </H4></center><HR>Created: 1995, August 1<BR>Revised: 1996, September 14<BR>Version: 002k<HR NOSHADE> <CENTER><H3>Background</H3></CENTER><p>All definitions begin from ignorance or lack of knowledge on a subject,and are part of the attempt to acquire more knowledge on that subject. Assuch, they begin as totally arbitrary, although based on the best knowledgeavailable at the time.</p><p>As more knowledge is acquired on a subject, and an attempt is made to corroboratethe definition in the surrounding world, a definition may change.</p><p>When a definition can be corroborated in nature (the surrounding world)and appears to cover all cases, have no exceptions, and can be used to acquireadditional new, moral and useful knowledge it trends toward becoming anabsolute. That is, not subject to arbitrary standards of determination.</p><p>I admit to an attempt to add humor to some of these, but without dilutingthe correctness of the definition. And, this is done also to reinforce thefact that current usage of most of the major, operative word definitionsrelated to our social structures is almost always ridiculous, irrelevant,and immoral. And usually irrational.</p><p>If you do not believe that proper and precise definitions--semanticprecision--is important, consider the case of petrol and sugar.  If Iarbitrarily define what most people accept as "sugar" is "petrol," and thenas you if I may put some of this "petrol" (actually "sugar") in the petroltank of our car, will you agree?  If not, and you believe that semanticprecision is not important (just playing with words), why will you notagree to putting what is in fact sugar into your petrol tank?</p><hr><CENTER> <H3>Types of Definitions</H3></CENTER><p>I have provided definitions based on up to three concepts for anything defined,depending on the past and current usage "Average" or "Political"usage, and what should be the future or "Normal" usage.</p><LI><B>Average Usage</B> <UL>	<p>	<cite>	That which is current and may be amoral, moral, or immoral.	</cite>	</p>	<p>	However, so heavily ingrained in our minds is the concept that interference	in the property of another is "okay" if the "majority"	agrees, that generally--more times than not--the intention involves an act	of property interference.	</p></UL><LI><B>Normal Usage</B> <ul>	<p>	<CITE>That which is current, and moral or amoral. </CITE>	</p></ul><li><b>Political Usage</b></UL>	<p>	<cite>	That which is immoral, and probably also irrational.	</cite>	</p></ul><hr noshade><CENTER><H3>Important</H3></CENTER><p>You must think about what you read--look and think about the world aroundyou--and determine in your own mind if the definition accurately and consistentlyrefelects what <B>really</B> happens and represents a true indication ofthe principles behind events.</p><hr noshade><CENTER><H3>Nota Bene</CENTER></H3><p>In the event that various political states and politicians, and any of theirsupporters, disagree with some of the definitions herein that involve themor their activities, I suggest a test.</p><p>If one or more of the subjects of a political state breaks a political lawwhich does not involve an act of property intereference within the rationaland moral defintion of property as defined herein, and such subject or individualrefuses to be accept the punishment prescribed by such political law(s),that no harm will come to such person if they refuse to accept such punishment.</p><p>If the political state insists on punishing someone for doing somethingwhich is moral but is "illegal," then that political state isconfirming and corroborating the definitions herein.</p><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H4>| <A HREF="#A">A</A> | <A HREF="#B">B</A> | <A HREF="#C">C</A> | <A HREF="#D">D</A> | <A HREF="#E">E</A> | <A HREF="#F">F</A> | <A HREF="#G">G</A> |  <A HREF="#H">H</A> | <A HREF="#I">I</A> | <A HREF="#J">J</A> | <A HREF="#K">K</A> | <A HREF="#L">L</A> | </h4>  <h4>| <A HREF="#M">M</A> | <A HREF="#N">N</A> | <A HREF="#O">O</A> | <A HREF="#P">P</A> | <A HREF="#Q">Q</A> |<A HREF="#R">R</A> |<A HREF="#S">S</A> |<A HREF="#T">T</A> | <A HREF="#U">U</A> | <A HREF="#V">V</A> | <A HREF="#W">W</A> | <A HREF="#X">X</A> | <A HREF="#Y">Y</A> |<A HREF="#Z">Z</A> |</H4></CENTER><HR NOSHDAE><CENTER><h2><A NAME="A"></A>A</H2></CENTER><H3>activist</H3><UL><H4>Average</H4><p><cite>An individual who plans or executes an act ofproperty intereference. </cite></p><p> One who advocates that the political state use its monopoly onpolice to promote the wishes and desires of the advocate and suppressthe ideas and wishes which contradict those of the advocate. Generallya person who has no original or moral ideas, and who produces no usefulproducts or ideas.</p><p> In a non-coercive society the concept would be known only tohistorians specializing in primitive, extinct civilizations.</p></UL><hr><H3>affirmative action</H3><UL>A phrase so imprecise that it is very difficult to determine what willbe done. However, when a person thinks in terms of <CITE>principles</CITE>it clears away all the obfuscation. <BR><BR>What is intended is to force someone or some organization to do that whichthey may or may not wish to do voluntarily, however the monopoly on policepowers of the political state will require the individual or organizationto do that which the political state wishes. It is merely another word fora criminal interference in the property of another, albeit a "legal"such interference. <BR><BR>See how clear things become when you use precise, consistent, absolute definitions?</UL><hr><h3>Air Force One</h3><ul>	<p>	In the German language this would referred to as the 	<b>F&uuml;hrerflugzeug</b>, meaning "The Leader's Aircraft" or	"The Ruler's Aircraft."  In this sense it is very much like Hitler's	<b>F&uuml;hrerzug</b>, or The Leader's Train, which he used to	visit the adoring masses.	</p>		<p>	It is paid for and thus owned by millions of	Americans, yet controlled by The Ruling Party Faction.  A primitive	concept under which those who pay for things find they do not truly	own anything, and of course do not control it either.	</p>		<p>	It is the modern version of, say, the "sedan chair," in which Rulers	of old were carried by their slaves to places where rituals of	self-aggrandizement designed to impress their subjects	are performed.  Where sumptuous banquets are arranged, again at	the expense of those ruled.	</p></ul><hr><H3>antitrust</H3><UL><H4>Average</H4><p><cite>A concept which--through access to the monopoly on police powers ofthe political state--an attempt is made to make certain that thepolitical state is the only organization allowed to operate from amonopoly position. </cite></p></UL><hr><H3>ascend to (blank)</H3><UL><p>The <B>blank</B> is usually some political office such as president,king, governor, prime minister, etc. Or it can be more general in whichit merely says "Ascended to power."</p><p>This journey is actually a <I>descent</I>, as all who travel in thatdirection go down in long-term history rather than up. If a personrelinquishes political office after having held it for only a shorttime and having done little damage, it may be said they have"ascended" from an immoral position.</p></UL><hr><H3>assassinate</H3><UL><H4>Normal</H4><p><cite>The act of murdering a VIP </cite>(Very InsignificantPerson).</p><p>Generally, only people who have reached high ranking in politics--whether,civil, military or religious branch, and thus irrelevance in history--receivethe accolade "assassinated" when they are murdered.</p><p>VSPs (Very Superior Persons), such as a person who had established a successfulbusiness, bringing people new, innovative, and high quality products ona cost-effective basis, someone who had discovered the cure for cancer,or any other person who lived a productive and moral life would generallybe said to have simply been "murdered." </p></UL><H3>Authorities</H3><UL><H4>Average</H4><p><cite>A convenient, anonymous entity to which politicalindividuals can ascribe ideas or actions, which are almost always immoral.And, when the idea or action does not win favor--which is almost always--allconcerned escape responsibility. </cite></p><BR>News media collude with the political r&eacute;gime in this matter by reportingthat "authorities" have said, not said, done, or not done things,without identifying the guilty party or parties. <BR><BR>This is little different than having houses, cities, palaces, and organizationsfor which there is no responsible individual, issue decrees, make statements,"float trial balloons," and assorted other such things. (no individualis ever "responsible" in the correct definition of the conceptin a political, coercive-based organization). [see <A HREF="#SAYS">SaysWho?</A>] </UL><hr><h3>[an] authority</h3><ul>	<h4>Normal</h4>		<p>	<cite>	An individual who has useful knowledge concerning a subject on	which they make a statement.	</cite>	</p>		<h4>average</h4>		<p>	<cite>	An individual who, in all probablility, has little useful knowledge	on a subject on which they make a statement.	</cite>	</p>		<h4>political</h4>		<p>	<cite>	An individual with coercive powers.	</cite>	</p></ul><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="B"></A>B</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H3>bias</H3><UL><H4>Normal</H4> <CITE>A preference for something, arrived at after theact of discrimination (qv). </CITE><BR><BR>See <A HREF="#DIS">Discrimination</A> in this section.</UL><hr><H3>black market</H3><UL><H4>Normal</H4> <BR><BR>As my Teacher said, <CITE>"...the Black Market is the moral marketin an immoral society." </CITE><BR><BR>Political societies are based in coercion, which is immoral. They controlthe factors of business and force businesses to participate in immoral activitiesby making them accessories to the activities of the state. <BR><BR>Those businesses who operate without political licenses and without payingtaxes have the opportunity to operate morally, albeit--as the state wouldsay--illegaly. However, as pointed out elsewhere, legality and moralityare normally mutually exclusive concepts. By doing this, the business isbeing a bit irrational, since they risk attack by the political state, althoughthis irrationality is a short term thing, lasting only as long as the statemaintains its coercive powers. <BR><BR><H4>Average</H4> <BR><p><cite>Any attempt to provide goods or services through a mechanism and ina manner which is not fully licensed and authorized by the politlcal state,and which does not observe all rules, laws, decrees, edicts and wishes ofthe political state, whether written or not written, or announced or notannounced. This includes the ability of the political state to make anything"illegal" on a retroactive basis.</cite></p></UL><hr><H3><A NAME="BLACK"></A>black, in the</H3><UL><p>Traditionally, this means that a business is making a profit. However,black is the color of death, and not a joyous color. And, the accountingprinciples associated with "being in the black" are those sanctionedby the political state--another black concept.</p><p>A much nicer color for profits would be red (see <A HREF="#RED">Red, inthe,</A> following), reserving black "profits" of immoral organizationsand as a relic and memory of the political state. </p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="C"></A>C</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H3>Carlsoncopy</H3><UL><p><cite>A photocopy. </cite></p><p>This is the name which should be used for a "photocopy," as itwas Chester Carlson who created the concept and the associated technologicalcapability.</p></UL><hr><H3><A NAME="CIT"></A>citizen</H3><UL><p><cite>An individual whose life and property is controlled by a politicalstate. </cite></p><p>See <A HREF="#SLAV">slave</A>, [syn] in this section.</p></UL><hr><H3><A NAME="COLON"></A>colonialism</H3><UL><p><cite>The situation in which one political state rules another. </cite></p><p>The classic image of "colonialism" is when a country such asFrance or Great Britain rule an African or Asian country. But inprinciple it is no different than when a North American sub-state--suchas California or New York--is ruled by the political state in what iscalled "the District of Columbia." The former is governed bythe notions and whims of the latter.</p></UL><hr><H3>common man, or common people</H3><UL><H4>Normal</H4> <p><cite>Morally acting individuals who do not belong toan organization that has a monopoly on police powers.</cite></p><H4>Average</H4><p><cite>All those subject to the will and whims of the political state exceptthose directly acting on behalf of the political state. </cite></p></UL><hr><H3><A NAME="COM"></A>communism</H3><UL><H4>Normal</H4> <BR><BR><CITE>A societal structure based on coercion, in which the political stateprofesses to own the means of production and all property. </CITE><BR><BR>Since theft does not confer ownership, the communist state-- along withall other political states--can only profess to own property. However--alsoas in all political states--it is backed by a monopoly on police powers,the <B>control</B> is complete. <BR><BR>There is no operative difference between communism, socialism, monarchy,democracy, dictatorships, etc. There is only a matter of style and semanticobfuscation with its associated fraud and deception, that presents a different<I>image</I> to people who cannot discern that there is <I>no differencein <B>principle</B></I>. <BR><BR>Communism is generally not hereditary, although in principle it makes nodifference, as with all the other systems the mechanism itself continues,regardless of the incumbent. In all political mechanisms, only the nameof the ruler changes but the mechanism itself continues. <BR><BR>See synonyms <A HREF="#SOC">Socialism</A> and <A HREF="#DEMOC">Democracy.</A><BR><BR>See discussion under <A HREF="Glossary.html">Communism </A>in the "Word&amp; Concept Discussion" section. </UL><hr><H3>competence</H3><UL><H4>Normal</H4><p><cite>The relationship of moral things attempted relatedto the success at achieving the desired objectives. </cite></p></UL><hr><h3>country</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>The modern term for a "tribe" or group of people ruled by a		chief</cite>.	</p>		<p>	This may include one or more ethnic or language groups, and	tribes may become part of confederations or "super" tribes.  Such	as the Los Angeles Tribe being a part of the California Tribe,	which may itself be part of a tribe, in this case the Great North	American Tribe.	</p>		<p>	The chief of such tribal groupings may have various names	depending on the language and ethnic group, with the person	being generically known as a "leader," the equivalent in German	being <b>F&uuml;hrer</b>, or in Spanish <b>Caudillo</b>.  In	American English they may be called "Governor" (something which	restricts progress and freedom of movement), or "President,"	sullying a nice title.	</p></ul><hr><a name="CRI"><H3>crime</H3><UL><H4>Normal</H4> <BR><p><cite>An act involving intereference with the property of another. </cite></p><p>Basically and rationally, crime is interference in the property of another.Yet in the political state it means doing something which is illegal, which--asstated elsehwere--has little to do with morality.</p><p>In fact, in the political state, the concept of crime becomes totally twisted.If you accost a private thief (one not sanctioned by the state), and preventthe person from interferring with your property, you are deemed "right"and perhaps even a hero.</p><p>However, if it is the political state which is interferring with your property,and you resist them, then you are deemed a "criminal" and definitelynot a hero. States are fond of calling such people thugs, criminals, terrorist,revolutionaries (a travesty on a beautiful word) hooligans (a favorite ofcommunist r&eacute;gimes), and other such things.</p><H4>Average</H4><p><cite>Anthing which violates a political law or the wishes of the ruler.</cite></p></UL><hr><H3>critic</H3><UL>One whose main occupation is complaining that something is not "right"according to them, or that there are no good and useful ideas concerningsome subject. Generally this person has few if any new, original, or usefulideas and would likely be a failure at any productive task </UL><hr><h3>cure</h3><ul><cite>The total and permanent cessation of all adverse symptoms relatedto a disease.</cite></ul><hr><H3>Czar</H3><UL><p>The title given to the political ruler of the ethnic group variouslyknown as "Russians." The individual bearing the title uses themonopoly on police powers of the political state to control the propertyand lives of others.</p></UL><hr><H3>czar </h3><BR><ul><p>The title often given to one who is subservient to the Ruler of a politicalstate, and who is deputized to act for the Ruler in the control of the propertyand lives of others. It is often prefixed by the name of the area in whichthe person is allowed to exercies the police powers of the political state,such as "economic, pollution," "energy," etc.</p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H3><A NAME="D"></A>D</H3></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H4>Defense Department or Ministry</H4><UL><p><cite>The organization of a political entity created for the proclaimedpurpose of defending said political entity. </cite></p><p>However, if such organizations were truly "defense" organizationsthey would not be needed. Practically speaking, they are all "War Departments"or "War Ministires," available to be used by the Ruler or hisrepresentative to enforce political decisions. A war is in fact a politicalsolution to a problem; when various politicians say they are hoping fora political solution they really don't know what they are talking about,since a war is a political solution.</p><p>What they are really saying is that they want the other poliical entityto do what the first entity wants them to do. However, if necessary, theruler of either political entity will do what it is illegal for a "private"citizen to do, and murder his opponent. Or, more correctly, representativesof his opponent, since the number of political rulers who have died in warsthey promoted could be packed into a Volkswagen or a phone booth.</p><p>It's normally a winning situation for the Ruler. He (men do have the advantagein this area) can send thousands or millions of his subject to their deathsand almost certainly survive. Perhaps even becoming a "folk hero"in the bargain.</p><p>Besides not having to worry about unemployment (for himself, family, andfriends), day care, the price of bread or postage stamps, the price of petrolor haircuts, and a myriad of other things. These are taken care of for TheRuler & Friends by grateful subjects. Grateful for not having to worry aboutdischarging the functions of their life.</p></UL><hr><H3><A NAME="DEMOC"></A>democracy<A/></H3><UL><p><cite>A societal structure based on coercion, with the state controllingvirtually all property. </cite></p><p>In a democracy, the <I>mechanism</I>--which is in effect a gigantic committee--isthe ruler, with a comittee-head as the ruling figure.</p><p>A society in which a minority, selected by the majority, rules all individuals,controlling their life and property. The Ruler--the nominal head of theruling group, and those composing the ruling group--change with time, butthe mechanism itself (the Ruler and a bureaucracy) continues. The coercivemechanism, sustained by a monopoly on police powers, continues and is alwaysthere to control the aspects of individual life.</p><p>The difference between a democracy, monarchy, and a dictatorship is notone of principle, but of style.</p><p>If you doubt that the political state in a democracy does in fact controlvirtually all property, think:</p><BR>  <LI>of the myriad of rules concerning what you can or can not do withyour own house   <LI>of the even more noticeable effect on your business property   <LI>of things you are not allowed to do with your money which are moral,but which are illegal.   <LI>of the vast amount of open land that the political state professesto actually <b>own</b>, as opposed to that which they subtley control  <LI>of the ability to exercise the "right" of "eminentdomain," in principles whenever, wherever, and however, they chose  <LI>of the re-zoning of property, which can make it worthless on the market,as well as unexpectedly valuable   <LI>of the fact that through the myriad of taxes, many piled on top ofeach other, the political state controls more than 50% of the results ofyour production.   <LI>of the property which you can not and do not own because more thanhalf of your ability to acquire property--whether it is land, a house, car,stereo, clothes, or whatever--is taken from you. Much of it before you evenreceive it, the rest of it taken if you want to acquire something with thesmall amount of money the political state decides to leave you with.   <LI><BR>  <LI>See <A HREF="#SOC">socialism</A> [syn.] </UL><hr><H3><A NAME="DEM"></A>democrat</H3><UL><p><cite>An individual who believes in political entities, wherein theactivities of all members of the entity are controlled through a monopolyon police powers. </cite></p><p>The difference between a Democrat and Republican is superficial and a matterof style, not of principle. They both believe in and participate in thecontrol of people and property through the mechanism of coercion. They bothbelieve in property redistribution through coercive means, differing onlyin which property and how much.</p><p>See also <A HREF="#REP">Republican</A> [syn.]</p></UL><hr><h3><a name="DICT">dictator</h3><ul>	<cite>	Any person who--backed by the police powers of a political	state--is authorized to  control the actions of another	individual.	</cite>		<p>	See also <a href="#PRES">president, political</a> [syn.]	</p></ul><hr><H3>dictatorship</H3><UL><p><cite>A society in which a minority rules all individuals, controllingtheir life and property. </cite></p><p>The Ruler--the nominal head of the ruling group, and those composing theruling group--change with time, but the mechanism itself (the Ruler anda bureaucracy) continues. The coercive mechanism, sustained by a monopolyon police powers, continues and is always there to control the aspects ofindividual life.</p><p>The difference between a democracy and a dictatorship is not one of principle,but of style.</p></UL><hr><h3>discriminate</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>To choose between one or more alternatives</cite>.	</p></ul><hr><H3><A NAME="DIS"></A>discrimination</H3><UL><p><cite>The result of the act of choosing between possible alternatives.</cite></p><p>A basic right of all individuals which, when interferred with, is a criminalact. Failure to discriminate indicates a lack of knowledge and mental ability.</p><p>Discrimination in concept and thought is, be definition, moral or amoral.Acts carried out as result discriminating are immoral if they result inan act of property interference, although if they involve only your ownproperty--such as your company--they are moral. Any attempt by another partyor organization to regulate or control the results of discrimination bya person are immoral in any term, and certainly irrational in the long termif not the short term.</p><p>In making a choice, which is what discrimination is, it is not immoral orirrational to "discriminate against" someone considered for ajob because of their lack of experience. It is also not immoral to "discriminateagainst" someone because of other factors, although it may very wellbe irrational. But in a truly free society, a person who continually madeirrational choices would bear the consequences in the market place, whichis the only moral "reguation" allowable for such behavior.</p><p>The North American political entity makes a number of acts of discrimination"illegal," which represents an interference in the property ofindividuals and thus is a criminal act. However, in the lack of logic ofthe political state, the individual who violates the immoral--and irrational--politicallaw is the "criminal."</p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="E"></A>E</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H3>economy, stimulation of</H3><UL><CITE>A unilateral action taken by the Ruler or Ruling Group to increaseeconomic activity. </CITE><BR><BR>Various methods for doing this are: <BR><BR>  <LI>bebasing the currenty by inflating it   <LI>direct devaluation   <LI>deficit financing of activites   <LI>financing products or industries which have an unviable market product  <LI>controlling prices of articles, often with the difference betweenthe controlled and free-market prices being subsidized, usually with analready-debased currency, further exacerbating the resulting long-term problems  <LI>temporary decreasing or reapportioning property theft and confiscation  <LI><BR>  <LI>Since these are all negative actions and non-solutions, they musteventually be reversed, thus ensuring the next recession. And the opportunitiesfor politicians to again become "heroes" by "rescuing themasses from their follies."   <LI><BR>  <LI>Those who have raised prices to try to recover from the debasementof the currency are called "greedy 'capitlists'," leading peopleto believe that it was "capitalism" that caused the problem, whenin fact it was caused by the usual combination of socialism and communism--controlof business activities through the poliical police mechanism, or outright"ownership" of what is purported to be a "business."</UL><hr><H3>ethical</H3><UL><p><cite>That which is moral and rational</cite>.</p><p>Contrary to popular believe, there is only one concept of ethics, whichapplies to <B>all</B> human activities. There is thus no need for the non-subjectsof "political" ethics, "medical" ethics, "scientific"ethics, "railroad" ethics, "sports" ethics, etc.</p><p>The only ethical act possible within a political environment is the actof stepping up to the ranks of "common man" (qv) with the intentof never intentionally doing anything immoral ever again.</p></UL><hr><H3>Executive Order</H3><UL><CITE>A decree of the Ruler, constituting an act of property	interference.</CITE><BR><BR>As an attempt to obscure its true character and make it appear more"democratic," the title--but not the concept--supercedes Royal orImperial Decree. </UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="F"></A>F</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H3>fair/fairness</H3><UL>As in "fair trade," and "fairness" in dealings betweenindividuals. <BR><BR><CITE>Access to nature unrestricted by the immoral act of anotherindividual, and with all resulting actions being moral." </CITE><BR><BR>This does not mean that in an advanced societal structure that certain thingswill not be "restricted," since many things will have owners.For example, desirable street corners, a chunk of the radio spectrum, amineral deposit, Disneyland, and a myriad of other things. <BR><BR>What it does mean is that the owner of an asset generally wishes to maximizethe return on investment. And, well-known, valid, and rational economicconcepts state that this will occur at a price which is "good"and "best" for all parties to any transaction. <BR><BR>The "win-win" concept of a rational, moral, and durable societalstructure, as opposed to the current "State 1, Victim 0" conceptof societies based on coercion. </UL><hr><H3>First Lady</H3><UL><p><cite>Successful attempt to reduce the position of the Ruler's wife to thesame level of irrelevance as that of the Ruler.</cite></p><p>An unsult to productive and morally-acting women, since it implies theyare inferior or subservient to the person with this title.</p><p>In true political societies, where the ruler is truly a Ruler, the Ruler'swife needs no title, as she need only invoke the name of her husband toobtain instant respect, action, admiration, envy--and irrelevance inhistory.  So in that respect she is equal to the person with the title of"First Lady."</p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="G"></A>G</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H3>Group of Seven</H3><UL><p><cite>A group of intellectual and historical </CITE>[and somewhat hystericaland pathetic]<CITE> midgets composed of Rulers and/or their representativesfrom seven large political entities. </cite></p><p>They meet periodically to attempt to solve the problems they and other Rulersand Ruling Groups have created for and among various societal groups onthe planet.</p><p>Since all their actions are irrational in the long term, and immoral inany term within the proper meaning of the terms, they can not accomplishtheir stated objective, which is to "solve" world problems andenhance the quality of life for all.</p><p>If there are any relatively positive results from their meetings and actions,they will be only short-term in nature, and lay the ground work for thenext events that lessen the quality of life for all individuals. Althoughas a relative thing, the perpetrators of the ensuing disaster for mankindfare relatively better than their hapless victims. Employment within theirgroup is usually always up, job losses down, and benefits and salary atleast as good or better than elsewhere. They have access to the best medicalcare, retirement benefits, and job-loss benefits. Plus, there are continuingold problems and some new ones which "require" their servicesand continued employment.</p><p>The group is composed of individuals who for the most part have never beenengaged in property creation, including any ideas of long-term benefit tomankind, and who are paid and supported by monies confiscated from thosethey purport to represent.</p><p>Or did all the associated taxpayers willingly, and with no fear from theresults of not "contributing," pay for them and their activitieswillingly?</p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="H"></A>H</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H3>history</H3><UL><H4>Negative</H4> <BR><p>This is traditional history, which is a continuous and virtually uninterruptedrecitation of property interference and destruction, in which the most successfuldestroyer rates the most amount of attention and space in so-called "history"books and encyclopedias.</p><p>Thus, someone such as Napoleon rates 30 pages in the encyclopedia Britannica,and Amp&egrave;re--a contemporary--rates only a page. Napoleon brought deathand destruction to millions and impoverished France and Europe for a century.Amp&egrave;re on the other hand, founded the science of electromagnetism,without which the modern world would not exist.</p><H4>Positive</H4><p>Positive history is the story of past actions which have created property,whether tangible or intangible.</p></UL><hr><A NAME="HONOR"></A><H3>Honorable, The</H3><UL><p>Since the United States decided to struggle along without a monarchy,they do not have the rich assortments of titles to apply to whatsubstitutes for their "nobility." As a poor substitute for"Majesty" and "Highness" they have chosen "theHonorable" as an appelation for those most empowered to interferein the property of others and control their lives.</p><p> A person must wonder about those who do not have this title. Doesit mean they are the opposite of "honorable," and thus"dishonorable"? Also, it should be noted that the title hasnothing to with the root meaning of the word and its reference to theconcept of "honor" and morality.</p></UL><A NAME="HY"></A><H3>hypothesis</H3><UL><p><cite>An uncorroborated explanation for a phenomenon.</cite></p><p>See also <A HREF="#TH">theory</A> [ant.] </p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="I"></A>I</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><h3>illegal</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>That which would violate a politcal law</cite>.	</p>		<p>	Since there is little connection between iegality and morality, the	subject of morality has little to do with the violation of a political	law.  However, it has a lot do with rationality, since it is rarely	truly <a href="#RATI">rational</a> to violate a political law, as it	invites retribution and persecution by the political state through their	monopoly on police powers.	</p>		<p>	Generally, that which is legal is immoral, and often irrational also,	while that which is illegal is generally <a href="#MORA">moral</a>	 and rational.	</p>		<p>	The only rational course for a person is try through <b.peaceful,/b.	means to reduce the market acceptance of politics as a viable	process in society.  Essentially an education process.	</p></ul><hr><H3><A NAME="IMPOS"></A>impossible.</H3><UL><p><a name="mt1"></p><p><CITE>The which would violate a law of nature.</cite>{<a href="#mt">[mt]</a>}</p><p>See <A HREF="#POSSI">possible</A> [ant.]in this section for a discussionof this subject. </p></UL><hr><H3>inflation</H3><UL><p>An increase of the volume of money and credit relative to availablegoods, <B>resulting in</B> a rise in the general price level.</p><p>Politicians, pseudo-economists, and others ignorant in economics have ahabit of saying that various price increases will "add to" orincrease inflation. Even the dictionary--not normally a repository of correctdefinitions and semantic precision-- has this definition correct (Webster'sNew Collegiate Dictionary, 8th Edition). It is first the act of debasingthe currency through various money-laundering acts, "monetizing thedebt," and assorted other tricks that requires businesses to raiseprices to compensate for the decreased value of the currency. The inflationcomes <B>first</B>, and <B>THEN</B> the price increases. But, if the politiciansand their apologists admitted this, they would shift the blame to the guiltyand deprive themselves of a scapegoat for their nefarious acts.</p><p>Part of the problem of course is with the primitive monetary concepts andassociated systems which exist on this planet. There is actually a superiorform of money which exists and is used, although those involved do not realizethis is what it is. This will be the subject of a forthcoming essay.</p></UL><hr><H3>Intellectual Integrity</H3><UL><p><cite>The ability of an individual to accept a new idea or concept whichis based on true premises, valid logic, and--if involving human interactions--morality,even though such idea or concept may contravene 'current wisdom' or personalpreferences. </cite></p><p>This is a very important concept in the creation and use of new and usefulknowledge, increase in the quality of life, and creation of a rational anddurable civilization.</p></UL><hr><h3>International</h3><ul>	<p>	More properly written "Inter-National," with the hyphen to	emphasize the true meaning of "between nations" or tribal	groups, "nation" or "country" being the current name for what is	historically a <b>tribe</b>.	</p>		<p>	Each such tribe being ruled by a Chief, with the current tribes	using many euphemisms for the word "Chief," such as president,	first secretary, chancellor, prime minister, shah, shahinshah,	sultan, etc.  In the modern rendition of the tribe, the position	of Chief and Witch Doctor have been combined, consolidating	the concepts of force and fraud under one person.	</p>		<p>	Some of the more advanced political groups do not use	euphemisms, preferring honesty with such titles as caudillo,	f&uuml;hrer, ruler, etc.	</p></ul>	<HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="J"></A>J</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H3>junk mail</H3><ol><p>This appears from two sources:</p><b><li></b><H4>Private, non-political-state organizations</H4> <p>Private "junk" mail may or may not be junk mail. It can be ofpotentially great value. "Junk" mail can be irritating to somepeople, but to others it opens a window onto the world. Yes, many thingsmay be thrown away without opening, and others after opening. But in betweenthose you can find information on new products or ideas. And not infrequentlyI find that obscure item for which I had long searched, either for myselfor for a friend. Or something totally new and of great interest.</p><p>You can chose to totally ignore this type of mail if you wish, even havingsenders or potential senders remove you from their mailing list.</p><b><li></b><H4>Political state organizations</H4> <p>This type of junk mail is irritating, almost always unwanted, immoral, andoften quite dangerous. You ignore it at your own peril, risking fine, imprisonment,and death.</p><p>You can not be removed from the mailing list of these organizations.</p></ol><hr><H3>Justice, the organization</H3><UL><p>A favorite euphemism for the main persecution [sic] organization ofso-called "democractic" societies. The organization normallycoordinating the monopoly on police powers of the political state.  Insome countries it is also called the "Interior Ministry."  The British usethe rather odd name of "Home Office," although this originated when therewas also a "Colonial Office," the police ministry for controlling theirformer colonies.</p><p>Although on the subject of British Colonies, I would like to say that mostof them were <b>much</b> better off under British rule than under theirown, home-grown tyrants.  As British colonies there was generally orderwith "civilized" control, and they were all able to support themselvesagriculturally, and in fact exported food.</p><p>As the organization which sanctions and enforces the coercion on which thepolitical state is built and maintained, it represents a travesty on theword "justice." The concept of justice is recourse by the individualagainst crime or criminal activities, yet such "departments" andministries are the main dispensers of injustice in political societies.</UL><hr><H3>justice, the concept</H3><UL>"Recourse from crime." <BR><BR>Bears no relationship to the capitalized version of the word. </UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="K"></A>K</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H3><A NAME="KING"></A>King</H3><UL><p><cite>Ruler of a political entity, with hereditary succession. </cite></p><p>This contrasts to so-called "democracies," in which there is a rulerwithout right of hereditary succession.  This is the concept of "theruler has not be re-elected, long live the [new] ruler," rather than "theking is dead, long live the [new] king."</p><p>See <A HREF="#PRES">President</A> (political) [syn.]</p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><H2><CENTER><A NAME="L"></A>L</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H3>laws</H3><UL><H4>Natural</H4><p><cite>A Natural Law is man's intepretation and understanding, and the associatedexplanation of the way nature works.</cite></p><H4>Political</H4><p><cite>Whims of a political entity describing how they wish their subjectsto behave under stated circumstances, which are then backed by deadly forceof the monopoly on police powers of the associated political entity.</cite></p><p>Nominally these whims are supposed to represent the wishes of the subjectsas expressed to their "representatives." However, in practicethe "representatives" do what they wish and tell their subjectsit is in their own best interests.</p><p>[Syn:] bill, decree, directive, executive order, initiative, measure, regulation,rule</p><p>Whims of political r&eacute;gimes, which--like political r&eacute;gimesthemselves--have no relevance in long-term history. This is illustratedby the fact that for millennia various r&eacute;gimes have had laws against,crime and war, laws designed to prevent unemployment and activities designedto defraud subjects of the r&eacute;gime, and assorted other (list) items.</p><p>Yet, as we know from history, these activities have been going on as longas the political r&eacute;gimes have existed.</p><p>On the subject of war, it is the professed desire of most politicalr&eacute;gimes to prevent war, and treaties designed to accomplish thishave been in existence since man conceived the idea. Yet wars and politicaldisorder continue as before.</p><p>This should give us a clue that political r&eacute;gimes--societal structuresbased on coercion--do not work.</p></UL><hr><H3>leader</H3><UL><H4>Political</H4><p><cite>An individual who determines what the majority of their subjects wantand then provides it to everyone, whether they want it or not, through themechanism of confiscation and redistribution of property, using the monopolyon police powers as necessary. </cite></p><p>Such a person is really a follower, and not a leader. A valid concept of"leader" can not exist in politics since the concept involvesinteference in and the control of the property of others. It is certainlynot new when they periodically raise or lower various theft mechanisms orvary the style and amount of their property interference and control.</p><H4>Normal</H4><p><cite>An individual who creates new and useful knowledge that is madeavailable to others on a mutually agreed basis</cite>.</p></UL><hr><A NAME="LIBER"></A><H3>Liberal</H3><UL><H4>Normal</H4><p><cite>Pertaining to freedom. </cite></p><p>The English word "Liberal" comes from the Latin<B> Liber,</B>meaning "free" or "freedom," with the suffix <B>al</B>meaning "pertaining to." Thus the word liberal means "pertainingto freedom."</p><p>This does not mean that things per se are "free," but rather thatthere is property sanctity, and that property each individual has acquiredon a moral basis is free from interference in or seizure by any person orgroup. And that they may use their property in any way they see fit as longas it does not interfere with the property of another individual.</p><H4>Political, or Average</H4> <p><cite>An individual who believes in property interference.</cite></p><p>Generally speaking, when people say they are a "liberal" or thatthey believe in "liberal" concepts, what they mean is that thepolitical state should indulge in all sorts of "give-aways." Givingaway property it does not own, such as that stolen outright in the formof expropriation, or obtained through the fraud mechanism of purchasingit with stolen property, ie., taxes.</p><p>These concepts of the political "liberal" have nothing to do with"freedom" except for the concept of freedom of thought. When translatedinto action they represent an act of property interference, a concept contraryto freedom and morality. The so-called "liberal"--or a personof any other description--performing such an action is a criminal. </p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="M"></A>M</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><h3>miracle</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	Any happening or event that would violate a law of nature.	</cite>	</p></ul><hr><H3>monarchy</H3><UL><H4>Constitutional</H4> <p><cite>A societal structure based on coercion in which there is a figurehead"monarch," with the police monopoly being controlled by someoneother than the monarch.</cite></p><H4>Common</H4><p><cite>A societal structure based on coercion in which the monarch controlsthe police monopoly. </cite></p><BR>There is only a difference in style, not principle, between a constitutionalmonarchy and the common monarchy. It makes no difference to those ruledwhether it is somone called "king" who controls their lives andproperty, or if the person is called <I>prime minister, premier,</I> orby some other title. </UL><hr><H3>money laundering</H3><UL><p><cite>The act of disguising or covering up the source, destination,and usage of money. </cite></p><p>It is clear from this that the act of "money laundering" canand is done by both the political state and private companies. In afree society--one not based on coercion--such actions are perfectlynormal. They are often illegal in a political society, but this ismainly because it competes with an equivalent, monopolistic act of thepolitical state. In any case, as stated elsewhere, the concept oflegality and morality are generally mutually exclusive concepts.</p></UL><hr><H3>monopoly</H3><UL><H4>Coercive (political state)</H4> <cite>An organization which offers the sole product or service of its type,and this situation is enforced through a further monopoly on police powers.</cite></p><p>For some products or services, use of the product may be optional, whilefor other products or services use is required, whether desired or not.Price normally bears no relationship to market conditions, and quality,support, and reliability are normally not considerations. No competitionis allowed.</p><H4>Normal</H4> <p><cite>An organization which has, by virtue of offering the highest quality,most innovative and reliable product, best support, and most cost-effectiveprice, become the sole supplier at any particular time. </cite></p><p>The monopoly would be the natural form of business in a free society, althoughthe position would always be open to challange if the supplier fails inany one one of the attributes which have led it to the present monopolyposition. When this happens, competition <B>will</B> enter the market.</p><p>However, in societies based on coercion, with all businesses being regulated--somemore than others--in an act of "doublethink" the politicians createmonopolies while a the same time railing against them. And, through theiruse of police powers they create cometition unable to compete, and thenblame non-existing monopolies for the failure. They encourage firms to growuntil they become "too" big, and then force them to breakup.</p></UL><hr><a name="MORA"><h3>moral</h3></a><ul>	<p>	<cite>Any action which does not represent in interference in the property	of another person.</cite>	</p></ul><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="N"></A>N</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H3>NAFTA</H3><UL><p><cite>North American Free Trade Agreement </cite></p><p>This should more properly be called NA<B>R</B>TA, or North American<B>Restrictive</B> Trade Agreement, since trade is still restricted. If therewere no political, coercive trade restrictions, then there would be free trade.</p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="O"></A>O</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><BR><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="P"></A>P</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H3>Paramount Leader</H3><UL><p>A vanishing breed in this day and age when political leaders are afraidto be true political leaders such as a Louis XIV who said "L'etat--c'estmoi." "The state--that's me." A leader who does what he wishesto do, and brooks no opposition or even discussion on the subject.</p><p>In the last fifty years the only true political leaders have been peoplesuch as the Shah of Iran, Charles de Gaulle, Mao Zedong, Deng Xiapong, andRichard Nixon. Prior to them it was Stalin and Hitler. With the demise ofNixon it seemed for a time that perhaps Jimmie Clinton or Bill Carter [Idon't remember the names of insignificant people very well] or some otherVIP (Very Insignificant Person) might don the mantle.</p><p>All political societies should have a Paramount Leader to whom the peoplecan look up to for guidance and the final solution to their problems anddesires, and bring order into their lives. That is what politics is about....</p><p>Truly innovative and great political leaders allay themselves with the topperson in rulership, and include in their titles such things as "HisMost Christian Majesty." Or, as Generalissimo Franco did, refer tohimself as "Caudillo de Espa&ntilde;a, por Gracia de Dios." Rulerof Spain, by the Grace of God. This is powerful medicine. It equates anattach on the ruler with an attack on God, virtually a heretical act, givingpause to the faint-hearted. And keeping the masses in awe.</p><p>The "Royal Robes" crown, and assorted other regalia worn by someof the great rulers of the past also served to separate them and protectthem from the masses Many modern rulers try to affect a similar "regal"position for themselves through the use of uniforms, sashes, seals, andother such things behind which they hide.</p></UL><hr><H3>Pavlovs</H3><UL>Named in honor of Pavlov and his animal associates. <BR><BR><cite>A person who slavishly follows the capricious whims of their politicalmasters. Those who--like faithful dogs everywhere--follow their masters.Following such things as economic "Leading Indicators," believingin the wisdom and power of the political state to forecast and control eventsand provide their subjects with the best things in life. Things they wouldnever hope to achieve without the wisdom and guidance of those born to rule.</cite></p><p>Such people will not buy consumer products or make business investmentsuntil politicians tell them everything is going to be great. And they retrenchas soon as "the warning signs" are announced for a downturn. Allof which become self-fulfilling prophesies.</p><p>This is an individual with continually deteriorating competence and a pseudo-self-esteembased on irrelevant and irrational factors.</p><p>An individual volitional being may be one of two types:</p><p>  <LI>A person who thinks and acts morally and independently of others.  <LI>A Pavlov.</p></UL><hr><H3>photo op(portunity):</H3><UL<CITE>An event at which at least two or more VIPs (Very InsignificantPeople), usually politicians, posture in a vain attempt to appear to bedoing something worthwhile, and to be important and relevant in history.</CITE><BR><BR>The number of camera operation sounds and photographic light flashes isgenerally inversely proportional to the true importance of the participants.</UL><hr><H3>political scientist</H3><UL><p>Something that can not exist, as it represents a contradiction in terms.The subject of politics has no universally agreed postulates on which itis based and has no agreed definitions to be used for effective communicationand creating additional new knowledge on the subject. Thus, it is a subjectthat is totally disorganized. A "science" is a body of organized,useful knowldge.</p><p>"Political Science" can thus not exist, and is a non-subject.</p></UL><hr><h3>Political Solution</h3><ul>	<p>	Of course there can be no solution to a problem caused by politics	(with the vast majority of man's societal &amp; social problems	being in this class) through the political mechanism.  Politics is	the <cite>source</cite> of problems, not part of the solution.	</p>		<p>	What politicians and other non-thinkers usually mean by this, is	that a particular problem should be solved through "peaceful"	means, rather than resorting to <cite>naked</cite> force.  I emphasis	the word "naked" because all so-called political "solutions"	involve the use of force, as that is the main,	operative-characteristic of politics.  The imposition of the will	of a guilty politician through the mechanism of the monopoly on	police powers.	</p>		<p>	And, a solution using naked force--such as the military--is of	course a "political solution," since--by definition--the military	is a branch of politics, and a part of the politician	mechanism and process.	</p></ul><hr><H3>politician</H3><UL><p>Politicians come in three types:</p><H4>civil politicians</H4> <p>The dominant coercive individual in so-called democratic societies,in which they control the lives of all others through a system of fraudand mind-control, and covert force. In the area of fraud--as opposed toforce--they compete with and utilize their religious brethren forcontrol of the masses through the mechanism of mind-control and fraud.</p><p>In earlier political societies, in which the tribes (politicalentities, now called nations, countries, provinces, counties, cities,etc.) were smaller, this position was occupied by a person with thegeneric title of "Chief." As the concept of coercion wasrefined, the Chief allied himself with the Witch Doctor.</p><p> The official cooperation between civil and religious politiciansfor their mutual benefit, and to the detriment of the specie, occurredat the Council of Nicae in +325. This was the same council at which--bymajority vote--mortal human beings decided on the "trinity"concept of the "father, son, and holy ghost." Defeating the"god is only god" faction of Arius, who was then declared aheretic and "excommunicated" from the ranks of officiallyrecognized religious politicians.</p><p>There are two basic types of politicians:</p><ul>	<h4>Those Out of Power</h4>		<p>	Their main activity is to criticize everything done by those in	power, saying how they will provide more and better "services"	to their victims if and when they come to power.	</p>		<h4>Those in Power</h4>		<p>	Their main acitivity is to dispense largesse and obfuscation as	necessary to assure that they stay in power. Thus they must	defend themsleves against the outrageous proposals to provide	even more things "free" to their victims than the opposition	proposes to provide.	</p>		<h4>Result</h4>		<p>	It assures the continuing decline of each societal group, although	people sometimes have the <cite>illusion</cite> of an increasing	quality of life brought on by advances in technology.  As the	politicans continue to try to make it unproductive to produce	things.	</p></ul><H4>military politicians</H4>In so-called democratic societies they are nominally subject to controlof their civil associates. In non-democratic societies they often have thedominant role in controlling their subjects, using first force and thenfraud (the reverse of the usual "democratic" r&eacute;gime) asnecessary to achieve their objectives. Although it should be noted thatdemocratic, socialistic, communistic, and dictatorship form of politicalstates are no different in principle, only in the style used for achievingthe objectives of the r&eacute;gime. <BR><BR>In earlier political societies, in which the tribes (political entities)were smaller, this position was occupied by a person with the generic titleof Chief. As the concept of coercion was refined, the Chief allied himselfwith the Witch Doctor. <BR><BR><H4>religious politicians</H4>Playing on the need of volitional beings for security in the sense ofunderstanding their environment and fellow beings, they offer pseudo-answers. Generallylacking the military force available to the other two types of politicians,they depend almost exclusively on fraud coupled with mysticism. <BR><BR>In earlier political societies, in which the tribes (political entities)were smaller, this person generally had the generic title of Witch Doctor.<BR><BR>As political entities have evolved, the function of Witch Doctor and Chiefhave been combined, with the political ruler employing both concepts (forceand fraud) to achieve desired ends. <BR><BR><B>General Comment</B> <BR><p>It should be noted that each of the three groups use the other two to gain greater control over their subjects. This results in vigorous competition, degrading the quality of life for all concerned.</p><p>Thought:</p><ul><p>Perhaps fraud is not the correct word, as it implies an intent to deceive,which is not generally true of the religious types, although certainly ofthe political types. Ignorance, especially that of history and the currentworld, is the main cause for what appears to be fraud.</p></ul></UL><hr><H3>politics</H3><UL><p><cite>The environment in which politicians operate. </cite></p><p>An environment that an individual must sink or step down into. </p></UL><hr><H3>Ponzi scheme</H3><UL><H4>Private</H4><p><cite>A scheme in which the "investment" money is not put to anyproductive use for the purpose of generating a return on capital. Instead,existing "investors" are paid a return on their money from new"subscribers." Some of the income may be used by the organizationfor purposes unrelated to the functioning of the scheme. </cite></p><p>This requires an ever-larger pool of new subscribers to service each previousgeneration of subscribers. When those receiving pay-outs begins to exceednew subscribers, the scheme collapses.</p><p>Participation is voluntary, and determination of the associated risk isthe responsibility of the individual.</p><hr><H4>Public (Political)</H4><p><cite>A scheme in which the "investment" money is not put to anyproductive use for the purpose of generating a return on capital. Instead,existing "investors" are paid a return on their money from new"subscribers." Some of the income may be used by the organizationfor purposes unrelated to the functioning of the scheme. </cite></p><p>This requires an ever-larger pool of new subscribers to service each previousgeneration of subscribers. When those receiving pay-outs begins to exceednew subscribers, the scheme collapses.</p><p>Participation is mandatory (under penalty of death). Risk determinationis unwelcome and considered irrelevant.</p></UL><hr><A NAME="POSSI"></A><H3>possible</H3><UL><p><cite>That which would not violate a law of nature</cite>.[<B>mt</B>] </p><p>Generally when people say "...that is not possible," or "...thatis impossible" they don't know what they are talking about. What theymean is "I don't know how to do it." And it may also be true that<B>no one</B> has the knowledge of how to do it at this time. But this does<B>not</B> mean that it is "impossible" within the correct definitionof the word. </p><p>In fact, most things are "possible" within a correct definitionof the word, and part of the destiny of any volitional specie is the searchfor things which are possible. They create "natural laws," whichis an explanation of what is possible, and often how to do it. Althoughwith very basic laws of nature it may require years or centuries to createall the "how to do it" explanations. </p><p>A good example of "possible" and not knowing how to do it is theaeroplane. Powered, controlled-flight was never impossible, it is just thatno one knew how to do it until Wilbur &amp; Orville Wright demonstratedhow to do it on 1903, January 17. There were in fact "learned"articles written by a famous American thought to be a "scientist"which "proved" that such a thing was impossible. And when theWrights demonstrated that it was possible, he followed with an article saying,in effect, "...well, it will never be 'possible' for an aeroplane tocarry more than the pilot..." The name of this individual seems tobe fading in history... </p><BR>See <A HREF="#IMPOS">impossible</A>.[ant.] </UL><hr><NAME="PRES"><H3>President</H3><UL><H4>Political</H4><p><cite>Ruler of a political entity, without hereditary succession. </cite></p><p>Although a Political President does not enjoy the concept of hereditarysuccession, and must go through a limited period of messy political voting,there is not difference in principle in the result of a "democracy"ruled by a president and a monarchy ruled by a king. The problem is thatthe <B>system</B> of coercive rule continues, with only the name of theruler changing. </p><p>See <A HREF="#KING">King</A> [syn.] </p></UL><hr><A NAME="PROST"></A><H3>prostitution</H3><UL><p><cite>In the absence of fraud or coercion, the moral act of one individualpaying another for sexual services. </cite></p><p>Prostitution, within the proper definition of property, is always moralas long as there is no fraud or force involved, and as long as the act doesnot violate any contractual agreements involving a third party. Whetheror not it is rational is something that is only for the participants todecide. </p><p>Any attempt by individuals not a party to the services agreement to interferein the performance of the agreement is of course a criminal act. </p></UL><hr><H3>public policy</H3><UL><p><cite>The policy and associated procedures of the political state aspromulgated by the Ruler and Ruling Party Group(s). </cite></p><p>Were it not for the Political State the term "public" would bea largely irrelevant term, as in a free society it makes little differencewhat the entire mass of people believe in, think, or want. What use wouldsuch knowledge serve? </p><p>Companies, and individuals proposing to go into a particular business wouldlike to know something of their potential market, so in that sense it wouldbe interesting to know how many people might be interested in a 100,000year voyage to a particular star system, and other things like that. But,unless they were in the education business or had children to educate, the"policy" or concepts of others in that subject would be largelyirrelevant. </p></UL><hr><H3>Producer.</H3><UL><p><cite>An individual who has control, or re-takes control, of their lifeand destiny from the political state and begins to conduct their life ina rational and moral manner. </cite></p><p>An individual who considers politicians and the political state to be asirrelevant as history demonstrates they are. This is an individual of increasingcompetence and self-esteem, creating a better and better life for themselvesand their loved ones.</p></UL><hr><H3>protection racket</H3><UL><H4>Average</H4><p><cite>Any of a number of variations of schemes wherebyan organization purports to provide a "service" to its customersin exchange for protecting them from future, probably adverse events. "Subscription"to the scheme is mandatory. </cite></p><p>In political societies this scheme operates in both the public and privatesectors.</p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="Q"></A>Q</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="R"></A>R</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><a name="RATI"><h3>rational</h3></a><ul>	<p>	<cite>Any action which does not interfere with or damage the property	or another person, and does not damage the property of the person	performing the act, retroactively, or in the present or future.</cite>	</p></ul><H3>reasonable</H3><UL>	<H4>Political</H4> 	<p>	<cite>That which the political state wants.</cite>	</p>	<H4>Normal</H4>	<p>	<cite>That which is moral and rational </cite>	</p></UL><hr><A NAME="REB"></A><H3>rebellion</H3><UL>	<p>	<cite>A revolt against moral or immoral authority, invariably	resulting in an act of property interference. </cite>	</p>		<p>	See also <A HREF="#REV">revolution.</A> 	</p></UL><hr><p><A NAME="RED"><h3>Red, in the</h3></p><UL><p>Traditionally, this means that a business is losing money. However,if a company is losing money, and is nearing "death," a much moreappropriate color would be black. Red is a joyous color and should be reservedfor companies making money.</p><p>See <A HREF="#BLACK">Black</a>, in the, in this section.</p></UL><hr><A NAME="REP"></A><H3>Republican</H3><UL><p><cite>An individual who believes in political entities, wherein theactivities of all members of the entity are controlled through a monopolyon police powers. </cite></p><p>The difference between a Democrat and Republican is superficial and a matterof style, not of principle. They both believe in and participate in thecontrol of people and property through the mechanism of coercion. They bothbelieve in property redistribution through coercive means, differing onlyin which property and how much. </p><p>See also <A HREF="#DEM">Democrat</A> [syn.] </p></UL><hr><A NAME="REV"></A><H3>revolution</H3><UL><H4>Normal</H4><p><cite>Concept or action which results in implementationof new and moral principles resulting in fundamental societal changes.</cite></p><H4>Average</H4><p><cite>A revolt against moral or immoral authority, invariably resultingin an act of property interference. </cite></p><p>See also <A HREF="#REB">rebellion.</A>in this section. [ant.]</p></UL><hr><A NAME="REVO"></A><H3>revolutionary<A/></H3><UL><H4>Normal</H4><cite>A new, rational, and moral idea or event, or a person who createssuch a thing. </cite></p><H4>Average</H4><p><cite>An individual who uses force and fraud against an established politicalentity to create a new political entity functioning according to the wishesand desires of one or more individuals fomenting the rebellion. </cite></p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="S"></A>S</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H3><A NAME="SAYS"></A>Says Who</H3><UL>  <DL>    <DT>"Washington says...."     <DT>"The White House says..."     <DT>"The city says...."     <DT>"The state says..."     <DT>"Congress says...."     <DT>"Capitol Hill says..."   </DL><p>How do you determine the guilty? An unidentified entity proposes ortakes a criminal action involving property interference and escapesblame for it. Something which ruins the lives of thousands ormillions of people or confiscates the life-time earnings of thousandsor millions of people. </p></UL><hr><H3><A NAME="SLAV"></A>slave<A/></H3><UL><p><cite>An individual whose life and/or property is controlled by another.</cite></p><p>Does it really matter if the person is 98% or 2% controlled by the other?</p><p>See <A HREF="#CIT">citizen.</A> [syn.]</p></UL><hr><H3>slavery</H3><UL><p><cite>The condition in which individual thought, ideas, or moral actionsare subject to control by another individual or entity.</cite></p></UL><hr><A NAME="SOC"></A><H3>socialism</H3><UL><p><cite>A societal structure based on coercion.</cite></p><p>See synonyms <A HREF="#COM">Communism</A> and 	<A HREF="#DEMOC">Democracy.</A></p><p>See discussion under <A HREF="#SOC">Socialism </A>in theGlossary of Terms. </UL><hr><a name="SOCIAL"><h3>social science</h3></a><ul>	<h4>Political</h4>		<p>	<cite>The study of societal structures and their operation</cite>.	</p>		<h4>Normal</h4>		<p>	<cite>A non-subject</cite>	</p>		<p>	The word <i>science</i> implies organized, useful knowledge.  Yet	what purports to be an area of knowledge is merely a collection	of facts from which no one who studies the area has been able to	draw any rationaland useful conclusions, from which any rational	and moral actions may be taken.  The corroboration for this statement	is that <i>homo sapien</i> has existed for about 50,000 years or so	and has <cite>never</cite> solved <cite>any</cite> of the societal problems of the	specie.	<p>		<p>	The concept of "social science" is therefore in such disrepute as to	make the term and concept ridiculous, and its usage rather	repugnant.  I much prefer the term <a href="#VS">Volitional	Science</a>, with credit to my teacher.	</p></ul><hr><H3>statesman</H3><UL><p><cite>A person who has reached the zenith of property inteference, withsupreme abilities in the techniques of coercion and fraud needed to rulethe lives of other volitional beings, and has thus reached the nadir ofimportance and significance in life and history.</cite></p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="T"></A>T</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><H3>The Honorable</H3><UL>See <A HREF="#HONOR">Honorable, The</A> </UL><H3><A NAME="TER"></A>terrorism</H3><UL><H4>Normal</H4><p><cite>An act of property interference.</cite></p><H4>Political</H4><p><cite>Large scale property interference by a person or group not part ofa duly authorized political entity and/or the act of property interferenceis not authorized by a political entity. </cite></p><p>It makes no difference who performs the interference, the circumstances,or if the act is approved or sanctioned by another person or persons orany organization. Further, the degree or amount of property interferenceis not significant to the definition.</p><p>Syn: <a href="#CRI">[Crime]</a></p></UL><hr><H3><A NAME="TERR"></A>terrorist</H3><UL><p><cite>An individual who performs an act of terrorism</cite>.</p><p>This could be a public criminal, such as a politician, or a privatecriminal.</p></UL><hr><H3><A NAME="TH"></A>theory</H3><UL><p><cite>The one and only correct [corroborated] explanation for a phenomenon</cite>.</p><p>See also <A HREF="#HY">Hypothesis</A> {ant.]</p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="U"></A>U</H2></CENTER>			<HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="V"></A>V</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><h3>VAT</h3><ul>	<p>	A vigorous and aggressive from of theft practiced in all European	tribal areas, meaning <cite>V</cite>igorously <cite>A</cite>pplied	<cite>T</cite>heft, although they euphemisitcally refer to it as	"Value Added Tax."  It is difficult to see from and to whom the	value accrues in this transaction, although it is certainly not those	from whom it is stolen.	</p></ul><hr><a name="VS"><h3>volitional science</h3></a><ul>	<p>	<cite>That area of knowledge which describes the creation, operation,	and maintenance of rational and durable social structures</cite>.	</p>		<p>	This is knowledge available, "on-the-shelf" knowledge, ready to be	used to solve the problems of the primitive, coercion-based societies	on this planet.	</p></ul><hr><a name="VOT"><H3>voting</H3></a><UL><H4>Normal</H4><p><cite>The moral act of selecting a product or service for yourself whichdoes not result in interference in the property of others</cite>.</p><H4>Political</H4><p><cite>The immoral act of selecting a product or service for yourself whichwill result in interference in the property of others</cite>.</p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="W">W</A></H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><h3>watchdog</h3>	<ul>	<h4>Average</h4>		<p>	<cite>	An animal which, acting on behalf of its master, attacks things	or other animals it is instructed to attack or does not understand.	</cite>	</p>		<h4>Political</h4>		<p>	<cite>	An animal which, acting on behalf of its master, attacks things	or other animals it is instructed to attack or does not understand.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	Political watchdogs come in many types: electricity watchdogs,	gas watchdogs, medical watchdogs, rail watchdogs, telephone	watchdogs, etc.  However they share certain attributes:	</p>		<ul>		<li>ignorance of their area of for which they act as a			watchdog;		<li>an ignorance of history;		<li>a misplaced belief they are doing something worthwhile;		<li>access to the police powers of the political state.	</ul>	</p>	<p>	Syn: regulator.	</p></ul><hr><H3>white paper</H3><UL><H4>Average</H4><p><cite>As used by politicians, this is perfectly good paper that has beenirretrievably soiled by writing immoral and irrational conceptson it.</cite></p></UL><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="X"></A>X</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="Y"></A>Y</H2></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><HR NOSHADE><CENTER><H2><A NAME="Z"></A>Z</H2></CENTER><hr noshade><h4>End Notes</h4><ol><p><a name="mt"><li>My Teacher</p><p>Referring to my great, wonderful, and best teacher, Andrew J. Galambos.</p><a href="#mt1">Return</a></ol><HR NOSHADE><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |<HR NOSHADE><p>&copy; 1995 - TheUniversal Salvage Corporation </p><p><I>Specialists in Dying Civilizations</I></p></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><B>Contact Information:</B><BR><p>E-mail:<a href="mailto:administrator@freedom-server.co.uk">administrator</a></p><hr><p>The URL of this page is:</P><CENTER>&lt;http://www.freedom-server.co.uk/Glossary.html&gt; </CENTER><HR NOSHADE></BODY></HTML>
