<html><head><center><title>The Freedom Server-Word Definitions</title></center>	<META Name="AU" CONTENT="William W. Morgan">		<META HTTP-EQUIV="KEYWORDS"		CONTENT="Galambos, government, coercion, capitalism, 			history, Bedeman, politics, economics, truth, rationality,			epistemology, morality">			<META HTTP-EQUIV="Reply-to"		CONTENT="administrator@freedom-server.co.uk"></head><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><hr noshade><center><h1>The Freedom Server&copy;</h1></center><hr><center><h2> Word Definitions</h2><h3>Second Edition</h3><hr><p>This page has been visited</p><IMG SRC="/cgi-bin/Counter.cgi?www.freedom-server.co.uk.Words.html"><p>since 1996, March 16th, although it was created on 1995, August 1.</p></center><hr></b>Created: 1995, August 1<br>Revised: 1996, September 14<br>Version: 002k<hr><center><h4>|<a href="index.html">Home</a> |<a href="Contents.html">Table of Contents</a> |<br></h4></center><hr noshade></b><center><h3>Background</h3></center><p>All definitions begin from ignorance or lack of knowledge on a subject,and are part of the attempt to acquire more knowledge on that subject.As such, they begin as totally arbitrary, although based on the bestknowledge available at the time.</p><p>As more knowledge is acquired on a subject, and an attempt is madeto corroborate the definition in the surrounding world, a definition maychange.</p><p>When a definition can be corroborated in nature (the surrounding world)and appears to cover all cases, have no exceptions, and can be used toacquire additional new, moral and useful knowledge it trends towardbecoming an absolute.  That is, not subject to arbitrary standards ofdetermination.</p><p>I admit to an attempt to add humor to some of these, but withoutdiluting the correstness of the definition.  And, this is done also toreinforce the fact that current usage of most of the major, operativeword definitions related to our social structures is almost alwaysridiculous, irrelevant, and immoral.  And usually irrational. </p><center><h3>This Section</h3></center><p>This section contains words from the social sphere which have beengiven precise, unvarying definitions.  They should be considered absolutewithin the definition of that word.  Unless otherwise indicated, thesedefinitions should be considered as the "normal" definition for theword, as explained in the essay on that subject.</p><p>Words which are explained in the Glossary of Terms will often berepeated here.  In the Glossary there is usually an explanation associatedwith the word, while here there is generally no explanation.  If yousee a word here and would like to read a discussion of thedefinition, please refer to the <a href="Glossary.html">Glossaryof Terms.</a></p><hr><center><h3>Important</h3></center><p>You must think about what you read, look and think about the worldaround you, and determine in your own mind if the definitionaccurately and consistently refelects what <b>really</b> happensand represents a true indication of the principles behind events.</p><hr><center><h3>Nota Bene</h3></center><p>	In the event that various political states and politicians, and	any of their supporters, disagree with some of the	definitions herein that involve them or their activities, I	suggest a test.</p><p>	If one or more of the subjects of a political state breaks a political	law which does not involve an act of property intereference within	the rational and moral defintion of property as defined herein, and	such subject or individual refuses to be accept the punishment	prescribed by such political law(s), that no harm will come to such	person if they refuse to accept such punishment.</p><p>		If the political state insists on punishing someone for doing	something which is moral but is "illegal," then that political	state is confirming and corroborating the definitions herein.</p><p>	If the shoe fits, wear it with shame.  If it pinches, think,	modify your actions accordingly, and go up in history--join	the mainstream of civilization.</p><hr noshade><center><h3><a name="IND">Index</a></h3><h4>|<a href="#A">A</a> |<a href="#B">B</a> |<a href="#C">C</a> |<a href="#D">D</a> |<a href="#E">E</a> |<a href="#F">F</a> |<a href="#G">G</a> |<a href="#H">H</a> |<a href="#I">I</a> |<a href="#J">J</a> |<a href="#K">K</a> |<a href="#L">L</a> |<br></h4><h4>|<a href="#M">M</a> |<a href="#N">N</a> |<a href="#O">O</a> |<a href="#P">P</a> |<a href="#Q">Q</a> |<a href="#R">R</a> |<a href="#S">S</a> |<a href="#T">T</a> |<a href="#U">U</a> |<a href="#V">V</a> |<a href="#W">W</a> |<a href="#X">X</a> |<a href="#Y">Y</a> |<a href="#Z">Z</a> |<br></h4></center><hr><center>[<a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a>]</center><hr noshade><center><h2><a name="A">A</h2></center><hr noshade></center><h3>activist</h3><ul>	<h4>Normal</h4>		<cite>	An individual who plans or executes an act of property	intereference.	</cite></ul><hr><h3>[an] authority</h3><ul>	<h4>Normal</h4>		<p>	<cite>	An individual who has useful knowledge concerning a subject on	which they make a statement.	</cite>	</p>		<h4>average</h4>		<p>	<cite>	An individual who, in all probablility, has little useful knowledge	on a subject on which they make a statement.	</cite>	</p>		<h4>political</h4>		<p>	<cite>	An individual with coercive powers.	</cite>	</p></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="B">B</h2></center><hr noshade></center><h3>bias</h3><ul><cite>A preference for something, arrived at after the act ofdiscrimination (qv).</cite></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="C">C</h2></center><hr noshade><h3>Carlsoncopy</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	A photocopy.	</cite>	</p></ul><hr><h3><a name="CIT">citizen</h3><ul>		<p>	<cite>	An individual whose life and property is controlled by a	political state.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See <a href="#SLAV">slave</a>, [syn] in this section.	</p></ul><hr><h3><a name="COLON">colonialism</a></h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	The situation in which one political state rules another.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See <a href="Glossary.html#COLON">colonialism</a> in	Word &amp; Concept Discussion.	</p></ul><hr><h3><a name="COM">communism</h3><ul>		<p>	<cite>	A societal structure based on coercion, in which the political	state professes to own the means of production and all	property.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See synonyms <a href="#SOC"> socialism</a> and	<a href="#DEMO">democracy</a> in this section.	</p>		<p>	See discussion under <a href="Glossary.html#COM">communism </a>	in the Word &amp; Concept Discussion.	</p></ul><hr>	<h3>competence</h3><ul><cite>The relationship of moral things attempted related to the success atachieving the desired objectives.</cite></ul><hr><h3><a name="CON">confidence</h3><ul>			<p>	<cite>	Belief in something based on rational reasons.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See also <a href="#FAI">faith</a> [ant.] in this section.	</p></ul><hr><h3>conservative</h3><ul>	<h4>Normal</h4>		<cite>		One who conserves something.		</cite>		<h4>Political</h4>			<cite>		One who conserves the concept that there should be political		entities wherein the activities of all members of the entity		are controlled through a monopoly on police powers.		</cite>				<p>		In politics, among the things "conserved" are:		</p>				<li> The "right" to make war and conquer places;		<li> The "right" to engage in what would be called "conspiracy"			if done by a subject of the r&eacute;gime;		<li> The "right" to seize property of the subjects of the			r&eacute;gime under concepts of "eminent domain";		<li> The "right" to "manage" (mismanage?) the economy;		<li> The "right" to maintain what is essentially a "monarchial"			system, in which "The ruler has been voted out, there is			a new one, long live the system" prevails;		<li> The "right" to operate at large and increasing financial			deficits;		<li> The "right" to do the same or different things that a			"Republican, Democrat, Liberal, Tory, Socialist," etc.			would do, while maintaining that it is a "different,			wonderful, new" idea, and will finally eliminate all			inequities and bring universal prosperity, etc., etc.				<p>		For all of these, the "right" exists.  It is up to the r&eacute;gime		to decide when, where, how, and how much, and to vary these		factors at their wish.		</p></ul><hr><h3>crime</h3><ul><cite>An act involving interference with the property of another individual.</cite></ul><hr><h3>cure</h3><ul><cite>The total and permanent cessation of all adverse symptoms relatedto a disease.</cite></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="D">D</h2></center><hr noshade>	<h3><a name="DEMO"> democracy</h3><ul>		<p>	<cite>	A societal structure based on coercion, with the state	controlling all property.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See synonyms <a href="#SOC"> socialism</a>, 	<a href="#COM">communism</a>, and 	<a href="#DIC">dictatorship</a> in this section.	</p>		<p>	See discussion under <a href="Glossary.html#DEMOC">democracy </a>	in the "Word &amp; Concept Discussion" section.	</p>	</ul><hr><h3><a name="DEM">democrat</h3><ul>	<cite>	An individual who believes in political entities, wherein the	activities of all members of the entity are controlled through a	monopoly on police powers.	</cite>		<p>	See also <a href="#REP">Republican</a> [syn.]	</p></ul><hr><h3><a name="DICT">dictator</h3><ul>	<cite>	Any person who--backed by the police powers of a political	state--is authorized to  control the actions of another	individual.	</cite>		<p>	See also <a href="#PRES">president, political</a> [syn.]	</p></ul><hr><h3><a name="DIC">dictatorship</h3>	<ul>	<cite>	A societal structure based on coercion.	</cite>		<p>	See also <a href="#DEMO">democracy</a> [syn.] in this section.	</p></ul><hr><h3>discrimination</h3>	<ul>	<cite>	Result of the act of choosing between possible alternatives.	</cite></ul><hr><h3><a name="DUK">Duke</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	A hereditary ruler of the regional area of a political state.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See also <a href="#GOV">Governor</a> [syn.] in this section.	</p></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="E">E</h2></center><hr noshade><h3>ethical</h3><ul>	<cite>	That which is moral and rational.	</cite></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="F">F</h2></center><hr noshade><h3>fabulous</h3><ul>	<cite>	Of or relating to fables.	</cite></ul><hr><h3>fair/fairness</h3><ul>	<cite>	Access to nature unrestricted by the immoral act of another	individual, and with all resulting actions being moral.	</cite></ul><hr><h3><a name="FAI">faith</h3><ul>	<cite>	Believe in something based on irrational or mystic reasoning.	</cite>		<p>	See also <a href="#CON">confidence</a> in this section.	</p></ul><hr><h3>follower</h3><ul>	<h4>Political</h4>		<cite>	An individual who determines what others wish and then agrees	to provide it through a coercive mechanism.	</cite>	<h4>Normal</h4>		<cite>	An individual who determines what others wish and accepts	that as guidance for their own personal life.	</cite></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="G">G</h2></center><hr noshade><h3><a name="GAU">Gauleiter</a></h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	Ruler of a political entity known as a "city" or district.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See <a href="#MAYO">Mayor</a> [syn.]	</p></ul><hr><h3><name="GOV">Governor</h3><ul>	<h4>Political</h4>		<p>	<cite>	Non-hereditary ruler of the regional area of a political state.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See also <a href="#DUK">Duke</a> [syn.] in this section.	</p>		<h4>Normal</h4>		<p>	<cite>	A device which controls rate of progress or speed.	</cite>	</p></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="H">H</h2></center><hr noshade><h3><a name="HY">hypothesis</h3><ul>	<cite>	An uncorroborated explanation for a phenomenon.	</cite>		<p>	See also <a href="#TH">theory</a> [ant.] in this section.	</p></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center>	<hr><center><h2><a name="I">I</h2></center><hr noshade><h3><a name="IMPOS">impossible.</a></h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	The which would violate a law of nature.[<b>mt</b>]	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See <a href="#POSSI">possible</a> [ant.]in this section.	</p>		<p>	See <a href="Glossary.html#POSSI">possible</a> [ant.] in the	Word &amp; Concepts Discussion.	</p></ul><hr><h3>immortality</h3><ul>	<cite>	The historical attribute an individual acquires as a result of	creating new, moral, and useful knowledge.  The degree	of immortality is directly proportional to the value of such	knowledge to society.	</cite>		<p>	The corollary to this is that no individual who engages in	property interference and destruction may achieve any degree	of immortality or remembrance in long-term history.	</p></ul><hr><h3>inflation</h3><ul>	<cite>	An increase of the volume of money and credit relative to available	goods, <b>resulting in</b> a rise in the general price level.	</cite></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="J">J</h2></center><hr noshade><h3><a name="JU">justice</h3><ul>	<cite>	Recourse from crime.	</cite></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="K">K</h2></center><hr noshade><h3><a name="KING">King</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	Ruler of a political entity, with hereditary succession.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See <a href="#PRES">President</a> (political) [syn.]	</p></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="L">L</h2></center><hr noshade><h3>Lawmaker</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	A person who creates instructions detailing how other	people are to discharge the responsibilities of individual	life, and prescribing penalties for failure to follow	the instructions.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	Besides being an interference in the property of others, and	thus a criminal act, this also creates a race of increasingly	incompetent people who become more and more incapable of	discharging the functions of individual life.  Thus requiring	more and more laws.	</p>		<p>	Syn: coercer	</p></ul><hr><h3>leader</h3><ul>	<p>	<h4>Political</h4>	</p>		<p>	<cite>	An individual who determines what the majority of their	subjects want and then provides it to everyone, whether they	want it or not, through the mechanism of confiscation and	redistribution of property, using the monopoly on police powers	as necessary.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	Syn: coercer	</p>		<p>	<h4>Normal</h4>	</p>		<p>	<cite>	An individual who creates new and useful knowledge that is	made available to others on a mutually agreed basis.	</cite>	</p></ul><hr><h3>Liberal</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	Pertaining to freedom.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See also <a href="Glossary.html#LIBER">Liberal</a> in the	"Word &amp; Concept Discussion" section.	</p>	</ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="M">M</h2></center><hr noshade><h3><a name="MAYO">mayor</a></h3><ul>		<p>	<cite>	Ruler of a political entity known as a "city."	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See <a href=#GAU">Gauleiter</a>[syn.]	</p></ul><hr><h3>miracle</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	Any happening or event that would violate a law of nature.	</cite>	</p></ul><hr><h3>monarchy</h3><ul>	<p>	<h4>Constitutional</h4>	</p>		<p>	<cite>	A societal structure based on coercion in which there is a	figurehead "monarch," with the police monopoly being controlled	by someone other than the monarch.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	<h4>Common</h4>	</p>		<p>	<cite>	A societal structure based on coercion in which the monarch	controls the police monopoly.	</cite>	</p></ul><hr><h3>monopoly</h3><ul><p><h4>Average (Coercive political state)</h4><p><cite>An organization which offers the sole product or service of its type,and this situation is enforced through a further monopoly on policepowers.</cite><h4>Normal</h4><p><cite>An organization which has, by virtue of offering the highest quality,most innovative and reliable product, best support, and mostcost-effective price, become the sole supplier at any particular time.</cite></p></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="N">N</h2></center><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="O">O</h2></center><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="P">P</h2></center><hr noshade><h3>policymaker</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	An individual who plans the concepts for an act of property	interference.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	Syn: coercer	</p></ul><hr><h3>politic</h3><ul>	<p>	fr. Gk <i>politikos</i>, <b>1</b> characterized by shrewdness in	managing, contriving, or dealing.	</p>		<p>	See <a href=#POLIP">politophile</a>	<p></ul><hr><a name="POLIP"><h3>politophile</h3></a><ul>	<p><cite>	An individual who believes in or has a craving for controlling the	lives and property of others without their permission, using	force or fraud as necessary as necessary to satisfy their	craving.</cite>	</p>		<p>	Individual politophiles often band together in the furtherance of	their activities.	</p></ul><hr><h3><a name="POSSI">possible</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	That which would not violate a law of nature.[<b>mt</b>]	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See <a href="Glossary.html#POSSI">possible</a> in the	Word &amp; Concept Discussion section.	</p>		<p>	See <a href="#IMPOS">impossible. </a>[ant.] in this section.	</p></ul><hr><h3><name="PRES">President</h3><ul>	<h4>Political</h4>		<p>	<cite>	Ruler of a political entity, without hereditary succession.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See <a href="#KING">King</a> [syn.] in this section.	</p></ul><hr><h3>prostitution</h3><ul>	<cite>	In the absence of fraud or coercion, the moral act of one individual	paying another for sexual services.	</cite>		<p>	See <a href="Glossary.html#PROST">Prostitution</a> in the 	"Word &amp; Concept Discussion" section for comments.	</p></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="Q">Q</h2></center><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="R">R</h2></center><hr noshade><h3>reasonable</h3><ul>	<h4>Average</h4>		<p>	<cite>	That which the political state wants.	</cite>	</p>		<p>		</p>		<h4>Normal</h4>		<p>	<cite>	That which is moral and rational	</cite>	</p></ul><hr><h3><a name="REB">rebellion</h3><ul>	<cite>	A revolt against moral or immoral authority, invariably resulting	in an act of property interference.	</cite>		<p>	See also <a href="#REV"> revolution</a> in this section.	</p></ul><hr><h3><a name="REP">Republican</h3><ul>	<cite>	An individual who believes in political entities, wherein the	activities of all members of the entity are controlled through a	monopoly on police powers.	</cite>		<p>	See also <a href="#DEM">Democrat</a> [syn.] in this section.	</p></ul><hr><h3><a name="REV">revolution</h3>	<ul>	<h4>Normal</h4>		<cite>	Concept or action which results in implementation of new	principles resulting in fundamental societal changes.	</cite>		<h4>Average</h4><p><cite>A revolt against moral or immoral authority, invariably resultingin an act of property interference.</cite></p>			<p>	See also <a href="REB">rebellion.</a>	</p>		<p>	See also <a href="Glossary.html#REV">revolution</a> in the "Word	&amp: Concept Discussion" section.	</p>	</ul><hr><h3>revolutionary</h3><ul>	<h4>Normal</h4>		<p>	<cite>	A new, rational, and moral idea or event, or a person who creates	such a thing.	</cite>	</p>		<h4>Average (political)</h4>		<p>	<cite>	A rebellion, using force and fraud against an established political	entity to create a new political entity functioning according to	the wishes and desires of one or more individuals fomenting the	rebellion.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See also <a href="Glossary.html#REVO">revolutionary</a> in the	"Word &amp; Concept Discussion" section.	</p>	</ul>	<hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="S">S</h2></center><hr noshade><h3><a name="SLAV">slave</h3></p><ul>	<p>	<cite>	An individual whose life and/or property is controlled by	another.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	Does it really matter if the person is 98% or 2% controlled	by the other?	</p>		<p>	See <a href="#CIT">citizen</a> (syn.) in this section.	</p></ul><hr><h3>slavery</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	The condition in which individual thought, ideas, or moral actions	are subject to control by another individual or entity.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See also <a href="Glossary.html#SLAV">slave</a> in the "Word	&amp; Concept Discussion" section.</ul><hr><h3><a name="SOC">socialism</h3></p><ul>	<p>	<cite>	A societal structure based on coercion.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See synonyms <a href="#COM"> Communism</a> and	<a href="#DEMO">Democracy</a> in this section.	</p>		<p>	See discussion under <a href="Glossary.html#SOC">socialism </a>	in the "Word &amp; Concept Discussion" section.	</p></ul>	<hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="T">T</h2></center><hr noshade><h3>terrorism</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	An act of property interference.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See discussion in the <a href="Glossary.html#TER">Glossary</a>	</p></ul><hr><h3>terrorist</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	An individual who performs an act of terrorism.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See discussion in the <a href="Glossary.html#TERR">Glossary</a>	</p>	</ul><hr><h3><a name="TH">theory</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	The one and only correct [corroborated] explanation for a	phenomenon.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See also <a href="#HY">Hypothesis</a> in this section. [ant.]	</p></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="U">U</h2></center><hr noshade><h3>unjust</h3><ul>	<p>	<cite>	That which exhibits a lack of justics.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	See <a href="#JU">justice</a> in this section.	</p></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="V">V</h2></center><hr noshade><h3>voting</h3>	<ul>	<h4>Economic</h4>		<p>	<cite>	The moral act of selecting a product or service for yourself	which does not result in interference in the property of others.	</cite>	</p>		<h4>Political</h4>		<p>	<cite>	The immoral act of selecting a product or service for yourself	which will result in interference in the property of others.	</cite>	</p></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="W">W</h2></center><h3>watchdog</h3>	<ul>	<h4>Average</h4>		<p>	<cite>	An animal which, acting on behalf of its master, attacks things	or other animals it is instructed to attack or does not understand.	</cite>	</p>		<h4>Political</h4>		<p>	<cite>	An animal which, acting on behalf of its master, attacks things	or other animals it is instructed to attack or does not understand.	</cite>	</p>		<p>	Syn: regulator.	</p></ul><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="X">X</h2></center><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="Y">Y</h2></center><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr><center><h2><a name="Z">Z</h2></center><hr noshade><center>| <a href="#TOP">Top of Page</a> |<a href="#IND">Index</a> |</center><hr noshade><b>Contact Information:</b><br><p>E-Mail: <a href="mailto:administrator@Freedom-Server.co.uk">administrator@Freedom-Server.co.uk</a></p><hr><center>Copyright &copy; 1995 - The Universal Salvage Corporation<p><i>Specialists in Dying Civilizations</i></p></center><HR><p>The URL of this page is:</p><CENTER><P>&lt;http://www.freedom-server.co.uk/Words.html&gt;</p></center><hr noshade></BODY></HTML>
