<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>The Freedom Server - Current Values in Society</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#fdfbfe"><P><CENTER></HEAD><BODY><HR NOSHADE></CENTER><H1><CENTER>The Freedom Server&copy;</CENTER></H1><H4><CENTER>Second Edition</CENTER></H4><P><CENTER><HR NOSHADE><A NAME="Glossary"></A></CENTER><H2><CENTER>Current Values in Society</CENTER></H2><H4><CENTER>1996, March</CENTER></H4><P><CENTER><HR NOSHADE><BR>This page has been visited <BR><BR><IMG SRC="/cgi-bin/Counter.cgi?www.freedom-server.co.uk.Current-Values-Mar.html" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> <BR><BR>since 1996, May 4. <BR></CENTER><P><HR>Created: 1995, August 1<BR>Revised: 1996, June 1<BR>Version: 002i<HR NOSHADE><H4><CENTER>| <A HREF="index.html">Home</A> | <A HREF="Contents.html">Tableof Contents</A> |</CENTER></H4><HR NOSHADE><H3><CENTER>Background</CENTER></H3>As everyone is aware, it is possible to argue about politics and religionat great length without any individual party to the discussion being convincedanother person is &quot;right.&quot; It is always a person's own politicalparty that is &quot;best,&quot; and that will solve the problems of society.Never mind that the problems never get solved. Since this seems to be awaste of time, how about another approach? <BR><BR>How about looking at the value received from what is commonly called &quot;politics,&quot;and the value received from what is commonly called &quot;science&quot;?And also from &quot;business,&quot; even if you might initially feel thereis no value to be received from business. And, if you feel that way, youmight consider whether the microwave oven, frozen food, a Sony Walkman,or the jet aicraft which takes you to your &quot;dream holiday&quot; isof any value to you. Those come both from &quot;business&quot; and &quot;science.&quot;<BR><BR>To do this we must define what we mean by &quot;value&quot; in society.How about keeping it simple and just saying that it is: <BLOCKQUOTE><CITE>Anything which has the potential for adding to the qualityof life of the individual. </CITE></BLOCKQUOTE>Thus, if something <B>will</B> or <I>may</I> add to the quality of life,and almost certainly will not detract from it, then it is of &quot;value&quot;to society. And, conversley, something which does not add to the qualityof life, and may very well make life worse, has no &quot;value&quot; forsociety. We must also bear in mind that value for a particular society isthe sum-total of the value for each individual in that society. <BR><BR>Please examine the following and see whether you feel people and activitiesin the &quot;Mainstream of Civilization&quot; offer the potential for addingvalue to your life, or if it is the concept of politics that will add valueto your life. <BR><BR><HR NOSHADE><H3><CENTER>1996, Month</CENTER></H3><P><CENTER><TABLE border> <TR> <TH>MAINSTREAM OF CIVILIZATION</TH> <TH>POLITICS</TH></TR> <TR> <TH>Hope for patients with spinal injuries.</TH> <TH>Crackdownon late payers.</TH> </TR> <TR> <TD> <BR><BR>Two American medical doctors, brothers Charles and Jay Vacanti, have succeededin growing nerve tissue. And, more importantly, they have been able to sendelectrical signals through the artificial nerves. <BR><BR>They have been aided for the work of Prof. Robert Langer of MIT, who inventeda plastic polymer structure which is able to mimic parts of the human body.<BR><BR>In their latest experiments, the Vacanti brothers filled the polymer frameworkwith donated human nerve cells and then fed it blood products and oxygen.The result was fresh nerve tissue, while the polymer--which is biodegradable--dissolved, leaving the &quot;rope&quot; of nerve tissue. Then, in a crucialexperiment, the brothers were able to send an electrical signal throughthe nerves. <BR><BR>&quot;We are just beginning to explore a new world,&quot; said Prof. Langer.<BR><BR></TD> <TD> <BR><BR>It is becoming a common occurrence for many companies--and especially largecompanies--to be late in paying their accounts payable. When the accountpayable is a small company with limited financial resources, this can bea disaster. It is estimated that perhaps 5,000 such small companies collapsedin the UK in 1995 because of such late payments. <BR><BR>Now the saviour of small business--the political state--will step in andrequire on-time payment. And, if such on-time payment is not made, theywill require publishing of the names of the culprits. <BR><BR>I agree that this is a problem, but the use of the police powers of thepolitical state has never solved any problem. They only create problems.Does anyone believe the conferences against terrorism, famine, poverty,etc., ever solves these problems? <BR><BR>The political state, and the concept that some person or group of personsmust control the property and lives of all others is the cause of man'sproblems. The sooner that this is learned, the sooner we can being to implementthe true solution to the problems of mankind. <BR><BR></TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><I>Daily Mail </I>(London)<BR>1996, March 11<BR>&quot;Hope for spine patients as doctors grow nerves in lab&quot;<BR>Page 1</TD> <TD><I>Daily Mail </I>(London)<BR>1996, March 11<BR>&quot;Crackdown on late payers&quot;<BR>Page 1</TD> </TR> <TR> <TH>David Packard Dies</TH> <TH>Bob Dole is Reborn</TH></TR> <TR> <TD> <BR><BR>David Packard, co-founder of Hewlett-Packard, Inc., died at Palo Alto, Californiaon 1996, March 26. <BR><BR>He and William Hewlett founded Hewlett-Packard in 1939 with a borrowed $538.Granted, with political-state debasement of the currency this may be equivalentto ten or one hundred times the amount today, but assuming it were one hundred,that would still be only $50,380. <BR><BR>The company now employees more than 100,000 people directly, and many timesthat number indirectly. It has created numerous entrepreneurs and millionaires,a myriad of inventions and products, and enhanced the quality of life formillions of people. <BR><BR>This is the legacy of David Packard and of a terribly crippled, state-hobbledand virtually ineffectual form of capitalism. Contrast this with the legacyof Mr. Dole and the political system, whose products are crime, pollution,inflation, wars, unemployment, famine, poverty, homelessness, continuallydeclining educational standards and medical care, and all of the other standardproducts and problems of political societies. <BR><BR></TD> <TD> Mr. Dole announces &quot;I'm the Nominee.&quot; That means thehe is vying with Mr. Clinton to descend to the position of Ruler of thetribal group known as the &quot;United States of America.&quot; <BR><BR>He has already spent considerably more than $538 in this quest. Before theelection he will have spent millions of dollars to put himself into theposition of controlling the lives, property, and destiny of millions ofpeople. And in perpetuating the political legacy of crime, pollution, inflation,wars, unemployment, famine, poverty, homelessness, continually decliningeducational standards and medical care, and all the other ills of socialstructures based on coercion. <BR><BR><B>Compare the worth to humanity of a David Packard and a Robert Dole</B>.<BR><BR>Interestingly, these stories appeared on the same page, in the same issueof the <I>International Herald Tribune</I>. <BR><BR></TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><I>International Herald Tribune</I><BR>1996, March 28<BR>&quot;David Packard Dies, Silicon Valley Giant and a Philanthropist.&quot;<BR>page 3</TD> <TD><I> International Herald Tribune</I><BR>1996, March 28<BR>&quot;I'm the Nominee, Dole Annouces&quot;<BR>Page 3</TD> </TR> <TR> <TH>MainstreamHeadline</TH> <TH>PoliticalHeadline</TH></TR> <TR> <TD>MainstreamStory</TD> <TD>PoliticalStory</TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><I>MainstreamPub</I><BR>date<BR>&quot;title&quot;<BR>Page</TD> <TD><I>PolPub</I><BR>Date<BR>&quot;title&quot;<BR>Page</TD> </TR> </TABLE> </CENTER><P><HR NOSHADE><BR><P><CENTER>[<A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A>] </CENTER><P><HR NOSHADE><BR><P><CENTER><TABLE border> <TR> <TH>MAINSTREAM OF CIVILIZATION</TH> <TH>POLITICS</TH></TR> <TR> <TH>MainstreamHeading</TH> <TH>PoliticalHeading</TH> </TR> <TR><TD> MainstreamStory </TD> <TD> PoliticalStory </TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><I>MainstreamPub</I><BR>Date<BR>&quot;Title&quot;<BR>Page</TD> <TD><I>PoliticalPublication</I><BR>date<BR>&quot;Title&quot;<BR>Page</TD> </TR> <TR> <TH>MainstreamHeading</TH> <TH>PoliticalHeading</TH></TR> <TR> <TD> MainstreamStory </TD> <TD> PoliticalStory </TD> </TR> <TR><TD><I>MainstreamPub</I><BR>date<BR>title<BR></TD> <TD><I>PoliticalPub</I><BR>date<BR>&quot;title&quot;<BR>Page</TD> </TR> <TR> <TH>MainstreamHeadline</TH> <TH>PoliticalHeadline</TH></TR> <TR> <TD>MainstreamStory</TD> <TD>PoliticalStory</TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><I>MainstreamPub</I><BR>date<BR>&quot;title&quot;<BR>Page</TD> <TD><I>PolPub</I><BR>Date<BR>&quot;title&quot;<BR>Page</TD> </TR> </TABLE> </CENTER><P><HR NOSHADE><BR><P><CENTER>[<A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A>] <HR NOSHADE>&copy; 1995 - TheUniversal Salvage Corporation <BR><BR><I>Specialists in Dying Civilizations</I> </CENTER><P><HR NOSHADE><B>Contact Information:</B><BR>E-Mail: administrator@Freedom-Server.co.uk<HR>The URL of this page is: <P><CENTER>&lt;http://www.freedom-server.co.uk/Adobe.html&gt; <BR><HR NOSHADE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
